00:12:46,980 --> 00:12:48,150
等等
A moment.

377
00:12:56,110 --> 00:12:57,110
什么时候发生的事情
When was this?

378
00:12:58,770 --> 00:13:00,040
昨天早上
Yesterday morning.

379
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:02,800
新娘的脸是什么样的
The bride's face, how was it described?

380
00:13:06,020 --> 00:13:10,270
"死人般惨白 嘴巴像道深红色的伤口"
"White as death, mouth like a crimson wound."

381
00:13:14,310 --> 00:13:16,430
诗意描写 还是真相如此
Poetry or truth?

382
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:18,980
很多人认为 这两种方式都一样
Many would say they're the same thing.

383
00:13:18,980 --> 00:13:20,160
对 因为他们都是笨蛋
Yes, idiots.

384
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:21,180
诗意描写 还是真相如此
Poetry or truth?

385
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:26,680
事发之后 我亲自查看过她的脸
I saw her face myself. Afterwards.

386
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:28,100
什么事发之后
After what?

387
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:29,730
是你
You?

388
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:33,240
还是我
Or me?

389
00:13:40,810 --> 00:13:43,620
莱斯特雷德 一个女人当众吞枪自杀
Oh, really, Lestrade, a woman blows her own brains out in public

390
00:13:43,620 --> 00:13:45,800
你还要我帮忙识别罪犯
and you need help identifying the guilty party?

391
00:13:46,210 --> 00:13:49,080
伦敦警察厅的智商再创新低
I feel Scotland Yard has reached a new low.

392
00:13:49,220 --> 00:13:50,720
这不是我来这里的原因
That's not why I'm here.

393
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:53,230
- 我猜也是 - 那个新娘 叫什么
- I surmised. - What was her name, the bride?

394
00:13:54,150 --> 00:13:57,130
艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂 昨天是她的结婚纪念日
Emelia Ricoletti. Yesterday was her wedding anniversary.

395
00:13:57,210 --> 00:13:59,060
当然 有人报了警
The police, of course, were called.

396
00:14:00,310 --> 00:14:02,760
她的尸体 也被送去了停尸房
And her body taken to the morgue.

397
00:14:03,100 --> 00:14:05,830
这是标准程序 你究竟为何告诉我们此事
Standard procedure. Why are you telling us what may be presumed?

398
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:09,670
是因为后来 发生了奇怪的事
Because of what happened next.

399
00:14:11,140 --> 00:14:15,010
几个小时之后 在莱姆豪斯
Limehouse. Just a few hours later.

400
00:14:26,780 --> 00:14:30,290
艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂的丈夫托马斯·瑞克莱蒂
Thomas Ricoletti. Emelia Ricoletti's husband.

401
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:34,900
我推断 他是要去停尸房 辨认妻子的尸体吧
Presumably on his way to the morgue to identify her remains?

402
00:14:36,510 --> 00:14:39,050
而之后 他发现没这个必要了
As it turned out, he was saved the trip.

403
00:14:46,340 --> 00:14:49,220
# 勿忘我 #
Do not forget me

404
00:14:50,290 --> 00:14:54,410
# 勿忘我 #
Do not forget me

405
00:14:54,550 --> 00:14:57,620
# 还记得那个少女吗 #
Remember the maid...

406
00:14:57,620 --> 00:14:58,050
你是谁
Who are you?

407
00:14:58,050 --> 00:14:59,800
# 那个磨坊少女 #
The maid of the mill...

408
00:14:59,820 --> 00:15:02,990
你为什么这样做 你究竟是谁
Why are you doing this? Just tell me who you are!

409
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:06,470
你听出这首歌了吗 亲爱的
You recognise our song, my dear?

410
00:15:07,420 --> 00:15:09,170
我在婚礼上唱过的歌
I sang it at our wedding.

411
00:15:14,650 --> 00:15:15,650
艾美莉亚
Emelia?

412
00:15:16,580 --> 00:15:20,170
你不可能出现在这里 你已经死了
You, you're dead, you can't be here, you died!

413
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:23,170
我美吗 托马斯
Am I not beautiful, Thomas?

414
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:26,180
是否和你娶我那天一样美
As beautiful as the day you married me?

415
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:28,550
这到底是怎么回事
What the hell is all this about?!

416
00:15:30,810 --> 00:15:33,240
你觉得呢 这位英俊的朋友
What does it look like, my handsome friend?

417
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:37,790
这是一场枪杆下的婚礼
It's a shotgun wedding.

418
00:15:47,650 --> 00:15:50,660
这场案子中 演绎了两次至死不渝
Till death us do part. Twice in this case.

419
00:16:08,890 --> 00:16:09,890
这案子真是离奇
Extraordinary.

420
00:16:10,910 --> 00:16:12,090
真是难以置信
Impossible.

421
00:16:12,690 --> 00:16:13,900
这案子棒极了
Superb.

422
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:15,940
当街自杀 诈尸杀人
Suicide as street theatre, murder by corpse.

423
00:16:15,940 --> 00:16:17,080
莱斯特雷德 你会宠坏我们的
Lestrade, you're spoiling us.

424
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:18,270
华生 拿上衣服和帽子
Watson, your hat and coat.

425
00:16:18,290 --> 00:16:19,690
- 我们去哪里 - 去停尸房
- Where are we going? - To the morgue.

426
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:21,230
一刻也不能耽误
There's not a moment to lose,

427
00:16:21,240 --> 00:16:23,290
虽然很少有人 急着去停尸房
which one can so rarely say of a morgue.

428
00:16:23,290 --> 00:16:24,700
那我就在这里坐着吗
And am I just to sit here?

429
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:27,500
不用 亲爱的 我们一会就饿了
Not at all, my dear. We'll be hungry later.

430
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:28,970
福尔摩斯 我有个问题
Holmes, just one thing,

431
00:16:28,970 --> 00:16:30,080
我能穿粗呢衣服 去停尸房吗
tweeds in a morgue?

432
00:16:30,350 --> 00:16:32,700
形势所迫 不得不为 华生
Needs must when the devil drives, Watson.

433
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:37,040
再会 夫人
Ma'am.

434
00:16:37,740 --> 00:16:41,240
- 我也是竞选的一员 - 什么竞选
- I'm part of a campaign, you know. - Oh, campaign?

435
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:46,240
- 妇女选举权 -你是支持还是反对
- Votes for women. - And are you for or against?

436
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:47,800
出去
Get out.

437
00:17:03,780 --> 00:17:07,030
他们又走了吗
Oh, have they gone off again, have they?

438
00:17:07,030 --> 00:17:09,870
我真不知道 他们过的是什么生活
I don't know, what a life those gentlemen lead.

439
00:17:09,870 --> 00:17:12,990
是啊 这些先生们
Huh, yes. Those gentlemen!

440
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:14,360
不要在意了
Oh, never you mind.

441
00:17:14,370 --> 00:17:17,470
差点忘了 这是给你的
Oh, almost forgot, that came for you.

442
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:30,770
哈德森夫人 请您转告我丈夫 我今天晚点回来
Mrs. Hudson, tell my husband I'll be home late,

443
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:32,860
我有点急事
I have some urgent business.

444
00:17:32,860 --> 00:17:34,490
没出什么事吧
Is everything all right?

445
00:17:34,490 --> 00:17:36,820
一个朋友找我帮忙
Oh, you know, just a, er, friend in need.

446
00:17:36,820 --> 00:17:39,690
什么朋友
Oh, dear. What friend?

447
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:41,610
英国的朋友
England.

448
00:17:44,120 --> 00:17:47,590
她说得也太含糊了
Well, that's not very specific.

449
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,720
停尸房今天谁值班
Who's on mortuary duty?

450
00:17:54,230 --> 00:17:56,470
- 你知道的 - 一直是他
- You know who. - Always him.

451
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:05,910
这是哪个白痴干的
Please tell me which idiot did this!

452
00:18:09,450 --> 00:18:11,530
这是为了大家的安全
It's for everyone's safety.

453
00:18:14,290 --> 00:18:17,030
这女人已经死了 半边脑袋都不见了
This woman is dead, half her head is missing.

454
00:18:17,050 --> 00:18:18,370
她谁都威胁不到
She's not a threat to anyone.

455
00:18:18,910 --> 00:18:21,830
你去跟她丈夫说吧 他就在那边的床单下面
Tell that to her husband, he's under a sheet over there.

456
00:18:21,860 --> 00:18:24,190
不管昨天晚上 莱姆豪斯发生了什么事
Whatever happened in Limehouse last night, I think

457
00:18:24,220 --> 00:18:26,460
我们都可以假定 绝不是女尸干的
we can safely assume it wasn't the work of a dead woman.

458
00:18:26,940 --> 00:18:28,850
更离奇的事都发生过
Stranger things have happened.

459
00:18:29,660 --> 00:18:30,660
比如呢
Such as...?

460
00:18:31,020 --> 00:18:34,200
就是 离奇的事
Well... Strange things.

461
00:18:34,220 --> 00:18:35,820
你这话说得像个孩子
You're speaking like a child.

462
00:18:35,850 --> 00:18:39,100
肯定是活人干的 他去哪了
This is clearly man's work. Where is he?

463
00:18:42,890 --> 00:18:43,890
福尔摩斯
Holmes.

464
00:18:45,610 --> 00:18:47,190
霍珀
Hooper.

465
00:18:50,060 --> 00:18:52,100
你 回去干活
You, back to work!

466
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:58,100
用你的把戏 来震撼我们吧
So, come to astonish us with your magic tricks, I suppose?

467
00:18:58,100 --> 00:19:00,770
你需要我注意什么事吗
Is there anything to which you would like to draw my attention?

468
00:19:00,770 --> 00:19:02,690
完全没有 福尔摩斯先生
Nothing at all, Mr. Holmes.

469
00:19:02,690 --> 00:19:05,860
您想待多久都行
You may leave any time you like.

470
00:19:05,990 --> 00:19:08,500
霍珀医生 是我请福尔摩斯先生过来的
Dr. Hooper, I asked Mr. Holmes to come here.

471
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:09,630
请你配合一点
Cooperate.

472
00:19:09,650 --> 00:19:11,110
这是命令
That's an order.

473
00:19:13,380 --> 00:19:14,890
有"两个特征值得注意"
There are two "Features of interest",

474
00:19:14,890 --> 00:19:17,310
正如你常在 华生医生的故事中所说
as you are always saying in Dr. Watson's stories.

475
00:19:17,310 --> 00:19:18,720
我从没说过这话
I never say that.

476
00:19:18,730 --> 00:19:21,090
你说过 很多次
You do, actually, quite a lot.

477
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:25,250
首先 这就是艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂的尸体
First of all, this is definitely Emelia Ricoletti.

478
00:19:25,280 --> 00:19:27,220
她的身份已经确定
She has been categorically identified.

479
00:19:27,220 --> 00:19:28,470
毋庸置疑 这就是她
Beyond a doubt, it is her.

480
00:19:28,470 --> 00:19:30,560
那昨晚出现在莱姆豪斯的是谁
Then who was that in Limehouse last night?

481
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:32,640
那位也是艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂
That was also Emelia Ricoletti.

482
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:35,470
不可能 她死了 她一直在这里
It can't have been. She was dead, she was here.

483
00:19:35,470 --> 00:19:37,320
她丈夫临死之前几秒钟
She was positively identified

484
00:19:37,320 --> 00:19:40,060
才确认过她的身份
by her own husband, seconds before he died.

485
00:19:40,060 --> 00:19:42,890
他没有理由说谎 也不可能搞错
He had no reason to lie, could hardly have been mistaken.

486
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:45,930
车夫也指认了 那的确就是她
The cabbie knew her, too, there's no question it's her.

487
00:19:45,930 --> 00:19:50,020
但她不可能 同时出现在两个地方
But she can't have been in two places at the same time, can she?

488
00:19:50,020 --> 00:19:51,160
没错 华生
No, Watson, one place is

489
00:19:51,160 --> 00:19:53,540
刚离世的人 只能在一个地方出现
strictly the limit for the recently deceased.

490
00:19:53,540 --> 00:19:54,430
我知道了 福尔摩斯
Holmes!

491
00:19:54,430 --> 00:19:56,160
- 她们可能是双胞胎吗 - 不可能
- Could it have been twins? - No.

492
00:19:56,730 --> 00:19:57,140
为什么
Why not?

493
00:19:57,220 --> 00:19:58,930
她就没有双胞胎姐妹
Because it's never twins.

494
00:19:58,930 --> 00:20:01,400
艾美莉亚甚至连同胞姐妹都没有
Emelia was not a twin, nor did she have any sisters.

495
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:04,180
她有个哥哥 四年前去世了
She had one older brother who died four years ago.

496
00:20:04,180 --> 00:20:08,180
有可能是没公开的孪生姐妹
Hmm, maybe it was a secret twin.

497
00:20:08,180 --> 00:20:09,840
什么
A what?!

498
00:20:09,840 --> 00:20:11,340
没公开的孪生姐妹
A secret twin.

499
00:20:12,760 --> 00:20:14,130
你听懂了吗
Hmm? You know?

500
00:20:14,140 --> 00:20:15,630
就是没人知道的双胞胎
A twin that nobody knows about.

501
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:17,680
整个案子可能都是策划好的
This whole thing could have been planned.

502
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:19,570
从怀孕就开始策划吗
Since the moment of conception.

503
00:20:19,570 --> 00:20:21,760
她可真是有远见
How breathtakingly prescient of her.

504
00:20:21,790 --> 00:20:24,690
- 不可能是双胞胎 华生 - 那你怎么看
- It is never twins, Watson! - Then what's your theory?

505
00:20:25,380 --> 00:20:28,090
更重要的一点是 你又是什么毛病
More to the point, what's your problem?

506
00:20:28,610 --> 00:20:30,630
- 你什么意思 - 你在害怕什么
- I... I don't understand... - Why were you so frightened?

507
00:20:30,630 --> 00:20:33,260
目前为止 还无法合理解释 你为何突袭我的酒壶
Nothing so far has justified your assault on my decanter,

508
00:20:33,260 --> 00:20:36,220
还有你为什么 要让人监禁一具女尸
and why have you allowed a dead woman to be placed under arrest?

509
00:20:36,220 --> 00:20:39,090
这个特征也很值得我们注意
Ah, that would be the other feature of interest.

510
00:20:40,590 --> 00:20:43,010
她手指上有血迹
A smear of blood on her finger.

511
00:20:43,010 --> 00:20:45,550
留下血迹的原因可太多了
That could have happened any number of ways.

512
00:20:45,550 --> 00:20:48,930
没错 还有一件事
Indeed. There's one other thing.

513
00:20:49,490 --> 00:20:51,080
这块血迹 是之后留下的
It wasn't there earlier.

514
00:20:52,260 --> 00:20:54,050
那边的血迹也一样
Neither was that.

515
00:21:04,620 --> 00:21:05,630
是你
You!

516
00:21:06,270 --> 00:21:07,170
还是你
You?

517
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,320
是你吗
You?!

518
00:21:09,320 --> 00:21:10,960
福尔摩斯
Holmes?

519
00:21:12,380 --> 00:21:17,540
吞枪自尽 子弹贯穿头颅
Gun in the mouth, a bullet through the brain...

520
00:21:17,550 --> 00:21:20,000
后脑被炸得不知去向
Back of the head blown clean off.

521
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:24,440
他是怎么活下来的
How could he survive?

522
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:28,460
是"她"吧
"She", you mean.

523
00:21:28,460 --> 00:21:30,330
什么
I'm sorry?

524
00:21:30,340 --> 00:21:32,290
不是"他" 是"她"
Not "He", "She".

525
00:21:32,290 --> 00:21:33,880
对啊 没错
Yes, yes of course.

526
00:21:36,330 --> 00:21:38,750
感谢你们提供这么有趣的案子
Well, thank you all for a fascinating case.

527
00:21:38,750 --> 00:21:41,920
破案之后我会发电报给你们 走吧 华生
I'll send you a telegram when I've solved it. Watson.

528
00:21:43,710 --> 00:21:46,080
虽然死因很明显是枪击
The gunshot wound was obviously the cause of death,

529
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:48,750
不过肺痨的症状也很明显
but there are clear indicators of consumption.

530
00:21:48,750 --> 00:21:50,210
验尸还是很有必要的
It might be worth a postmortem.

531
00:21:50,210 --> 00:21:52,330
我们得尽可能 多收集一点信息
We need all the information we can get.

532
00:21:52,330 --> 00:21:55,250
老爸一走 他就有火眼金睛了
Oh, isn't he observant, now that Daddy's gone!

533
00:21:59,460 --> 00:22:02,150
在某些方面 我的观察力很敏锐
I AM observant in some ways,

534
00:22:02,150 --> 00:22:06,000
就像福尔摩斯 在某些方面很迟钝一样
just as Holmes is quite blind in others.

535
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:07,570
是吗
Really?

536
00:22:07,570 --> 00:22:09,600
没错
Yes, really.

537
00:22:10,830 --> 00:22:15,010
你想在男权社会出人头地 也真是不容易啊
Amazing... what one has to do to get ahead in a man's world.

538
00:22:24,290 --> 00:22:26,290
他这话是什么意思
What's he saying that for?

539
00:22:26,290 --> 00:22:27,830
回去干活
Get back to work!

540
00:22:35,580 --> 00:22:39,370
福尔摩斯 说说吧 你肯定有想法了
Well, Holmes? Surely you must have some theory?

541
00:22:39,370 --> 00:22:44,850
还没有 这个案子深不可测 华生 深不可测
Not yet. These are deep waters, Watson, deep waters.

542
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:49,780
但我必须深入调查
And I shall have to go deeper still.

543
00:22:58,580 --> 00:23:01,500
"不出几个月之后 我们再次
"It was not for several months that we were to pick up"

544
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:04,410
被牵扯到这个奇案之中
"The threads of this strange case again."

545
00:23:04,420 --> 00:23:08,620
案情也变得更加出乎意料"
"And then under very unexpected circumstances."

546
00:23:08,620 --> 00:23:12,310
现在已经有五起案子了 全都一模一样
Five of them now, all the same, every one of them.

547
00:23:12,310 --> 00:23:14,830
别说话 我在阅读很重要的资料
Hush, please, this is a matter of supreme importance.

548
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:15,420
什么资料
What is?

549
00:23:15,420 --> 00:23:17,820
黄赤交角的问题 我得搞明白才行
The obliquity of the ecliptic. I have to understand it.

550
00:23:18,050 --> 00:23:19,050
那是什么东西
What is it?

551
00:23:19,070 --> 00:23:21,190
我也不知道 我正在努力学呢
I don't know, I'm still trying to understand it.

552
00:23:21,210 --> 00:23:22,700
我还以为你无所不知呢
I thought you understood everything.

553
00:23:22,840 --> 00:23:23,880
当然不是了
Of course not, that would be

554
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:25,660
那多浪费我的大脑空间 我有专攻领域
an appalling waste of brain space. I specialise.

555
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:26,850
那你为什么学黄赤交角
And what's so important about this?

556
00:23:26,850 --> 00:23:29,600
那我为何要关心 五起无聊的谋杀案
What's so important about five boring murders?

557
00:23:29,660 --> 00:23:31,680
这怎么无聊了 五个男人
They're not boring. Five men dead,

558
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:34,410
在自己家中被杀 地上撒满大米
murdered in their own homes, rice on the floor

559
00:23:34,410 --> 00:23:35,770
像婚礼现场一样
like at a wedding, and

560
00:23:35,770 --> 00:23:38,500
墙上还用血写着"你"
the word "You" Written in blood on the wall!

561
00:23:39,620 --> 00:23:44,290
就是她 就是那个新娘干的 她不知怎么就复活了
It's, it's her, it's the Bride. Somehow she's risen again.

562
00:23:44,290 --> 00:23:47,540
- 我破案了 - 你怎么可能破案了
- Solved it. - You can't have solved it!

563
00:23:47,540 --> 00:23:49,490
我当然破案了 答案多简单啊
Of course I've solved it, it's perfectly simple.

564
00:23:49,490 --> 00:23:51,870
神秘的瑞克莱蒂夫人杀人案 凶手
The incident of the mysterious Mrs. Ricoletti, the killer from

565
00:23:51,870 --> 00:23:54,270
是来自阴间的鬼魂 从此被媒体大肆渲染
beyond the grave, has been widely reported in the popular press.

566
00:23:54,270 --> 00:23:56,770
刚好凶手可以用鬼魂的传说
Now people are disguising their own dull little murders as the

567
00:23:56,770 --> 00:23:59,310
掩盖自己卑劣的杀人计谋
work of a ghost, to confuse

568
00:23:59,310 --> 00:24:00,950
还能迷惑 愚蠢低能的伦敦警察厅
the impossibly imbecilic Scotland Yard.

569
00:24:01,290 --> 00:24:02,570
你看 我破案了
There you are, solved.

570
00:24:02,580 --> 00:24:04,390
你出门的时候 去拜访下哈德森夫人
Pay Mrs. Hudson a visit on your way out,

571
00:24:04,390 --> 00:24:05,620
她喜欢有参与感
she likes to feel involved.

572
00:24:05,620 --> 00:24:07,280
你确定吗
You sure?

573
00:24:07,280 --> 00:24:10,410
当然 你快走吧 华生 我准备好了
Certainly. Go away. Watson! I'm ready.

574
00:24:10,410 --> 00:24:14,240
带上帽子穿好鞋 我们有个重要的约会
Your hat and boots, we have an important appointment.

575
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:17,820
华生医生不是几个月之前就搬走了吗
Didn't Dr. Watson move out a few months ago?

576
00:24:17,820 --> 00:24:19,660
对 他搬走了
He did, didn't he?

577
00:24:19,660 --> 00:24:21,610
那我一直都是跟谁说话呢
Who have I been talking to all this time?

578
00:24:22,550 --> 00:24:23,450
请允许我代表
Well, speaking on behalf

579
00:24:23,450 --> 00:24:25,030
愚蠢低能的伦敦警察厅说上一句
of the impossibly imbecilic Scotland Yard,

580
00:24:25,030 --> 00:24:27,450
那个椅子上一直都没人
that chair is definitely empty.

581
00:24:28,490 --> 00:24:32,610
确实没人 不过刚刚的画面还不错
It is, isn't it? Works surprisingly well, though.

582
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:34,680
我还以为他能有所进步呢
I actually thought he was improving.

583
00:25:11,610 --> 00:25:13,520
你去哪里了
Ah. Where have you been?

584
00:25:13,530 --> 00:25:15,660
抱歉 先生 我今早起晚了
Sorry, sir, I'm rather behind my time this morning.

585
00:25:15,660 --> 00:25:18,610
你连鸡蛋都不会煮吗
Are you incapable of boiling an egg?!

586
00:25:18,610 --> 00:25:21,230
火也基本没点 到处都是灰尘
The fires are rarely lit, there is dust everywhere

587
00:25:21,230 --> 00:25:23,920
而且你在给靴子清泥的时候 差点把它毁了
and you almost destroyed my boots scraping the mud off them.

588
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:25,780
要不是我妻子负责
If it wasn't my wife's business

589
00:25:25,780 --> 00:25:27,730
管理佣人 我早就亲自管教你了
to deal with the staff, I would talk to you myself.

590
00:25:27,730 --> 00:25:28,860
我妻子人呢
Where is my wife?

591
00:25:29,350 --> 00:25:31,140
抱歉 先生 夫人出去了
Begging your pardon, sir, but the mistress has gone out.

592
00:25:31,230 --> 00:25:33,270
- 一大早就出门了 - 是的 先生
- Out? At this hour of the morning? - Yes, sir.

593
00:25:33,670 --> 00:25:34,670
您不知道吗 先生
Did you not know that, sir?

594
00:25:34,690 --> 00:25:37,060
她去哪里了 她最近怎么总出门
Where did she go? She's always out these days.

595
00:25:37,060 --> 00:25:39,230
您不也一样 先生
Not unlike yourself... sir.

596
00:25:39,850 --> 00:25:40,850
你说什么
I'm sorry...?

597
00:25:40,940 --> 00:25:42,400
只是我自己的观察 先生
Just observing, sir.

598
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:44,080
够了 谁让你观察了
Well, that's quite enough, nobody asked you to be observant.

599
00:25:44,190 --> 00:25:45,290
抱歉 先生 我只是注意到
Sorry, sir, I just meant

600
00:25:45,290 --> 00:25:47,440
你们现在很少一起在家 先生
you're hardly ever home together any more, sir.

601
00:25:47,900 --> 00:25:49,940
你现在的言行近乎无礼
You are dangerously close to impertinence.

602
00:25:49,940 --> 00:25:52,940
我会告诉我妻子 让她好好管教你
I shall have a word with my wife to have a word with you.

603
00:25:52,940 --> 00:25:56,480
好的 先生 您什么时候能见到夫人呢
Very good, sir. And when will you be seeing her?

604
00:25:57,230 --> 00:25:58,230
你听着
Now, listen...

605
00:25:58,250 --> 00:26:01,270
我差点忘了 先生 这有封您的电报
Oh, I nearly forgot, sir. A telegram came for you.

606
00:26:01,290 --> 00:26:01,860
你忘了
You forgot?!

607
00:26:02,190 --> 00:26:05,020
- 不是 我差点忘了 - 你这一早上都干什么了
- No, I nearly forgot. - What have you been doing all morning?

608
00:26:05,020 --> 00:26:06,980
读您在"斯特兰报"刊登的新故事 先生
Reading your new one in The Strand, sir.

609
00:26:08,080 --> 00:26:09,080
你喜欢我的新故事吗
Did you enjoy it?

610
00:26:09,350 --> 00:26:11,020
您为什么没提到我呢 先生
Why do you never mention me, sir?

611
00:26:11,020 --> 00:26:12,600
下去吧
Go away.

612
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:31,390
- 你说什么 - 我说黄赤交角
- The what of the what? - The obliquity of the ecliptic.

613
00:26:31,390 --> 00:26:33,770
你说"速来" 我还以为是很重要的事
"Come at once," You said. I assumed it was important.

614
00:26:33,770 --> 00:26:35,100
是很重要
It is.

615
00:26:35,100 --> 00:26:36,150
黄赤交角就是
It's the inclination of

616
00:26:36,150 --> 00:26:38,060
地球的赤道面 与其绕太阳运行的
the earth's equator to the path of the sun

617
00:26:38,080 --> 00:26:39,080
轨道平面的夹角
on the celestial plane.

618
00:26:39,090 --> 00:26:41,170
你刚学的吗
You been swotting up?

619
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:42,680
- 我为什么要学那个 - 为了显得你聪明
- Why would I do that? - To sound clever.

620
00:26:42,700 --> 00:26:44,570
- 我本来就很聪明 - 我明白了
- I am clever. - Oh, oh, I see.

621
00:26:45,030 --> 00:26:46,030
你明白什么了
You see what?

622
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:50,650
我推测 我们是要去见一个 比你聪明的人
I deduce we're on our way to see someone cleverer than you.

623
00:26:52,100 --> 00:26:53,720
闭嘴
Shut up.

624
00:28:07,090 --> 00:28:09,000
抱歉 你说什么
Sorry, what?

625
00:28:26,960 --> 00:28:30,860
如果你想研究人类 这里是最合适的地方
To anyone who wishes to study mankind, this is the spot.

626
00:28:30,860 --> 00:28:31,710
对你来说 也很方便
Handy really, as your

627
00:28:31,710 --> 00:28:34,250
毕竟你不断膨胀的屁股 已经永远粘在这里了
ever-expanding backside is permanently glued to it.

628
00:28:34,280 --> 00:28:37,690
- 早上好 哥哥 -夏洛克 华生医生
- Good morning, brother mine. - Sherlock. Dr. Watson.

629
00:28:38,790 --> 00:28:40,500
你看起来 很不错 先生
You look... well, sir.

630
00:28:40,530 --> 00:28:42,950
是吗 我以为自己看起来很臃肿
Really? I rather thought I looked enormous.

631
00:28:43,330 --> 00:28:45,870
既然您提到了 这种暴饮暴食的行为
Well, now you mention it, this level of consumption

632
00:28:45,880 --> 00:28:49,710
对您健康的危害极大
is incredibly injurious to your health.

633
00:28:49,710 --> 00:28:50,510
您的心脏
Your heart...

634
00:28:50,550 --> 00:28:51,860
- 不必为此担忧 华生 - 没必要吗
- No need to worry on that score, Watson. - No?

635
00:28:51,860 --> 00:28:54,320
他装心脏的地方 本来就是个空腔
There's only a large cavity where that organ should reside.

636
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:57,910
- 这是家族病 - 我没有指责你的意思
- It's a family trait. - Oh, I wasn't being critical.

637
00:28:57,920 --> 00:28:59,200
如果你继续这样生活
If you continue like this,

638
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:01,120
先生 我估计您最多能活五年
sir, I give you five years at the most.

639
00:29:01,120 --> 00:29:04,310
- 五年 - 我们以为只有三年呢 是吧 夏洛克
- Five? - We thought three, did we not, Sherlock?

640
00:29:04,310 --> 00:29:05,690
我还是倾向于四年
I'm still inclined to four.

641
00:29:05,790 --> 00:29:07,790
你还是这样 只会看 不懂得观察
As ever, you see but you do not observe.

642
00:29:07,790 --> 00:29:10,370
注意我眼白的颜色发生了变化
Note the discolouration in the whites of my eyes,

643
00:29:10,370 --> 00:29:12,290
角膜周围出现可见的脂肪圈
the visible rings of fat around the corneas.

644
00:29:12,350 --> 00:29:13,600
没错 你说得有道理
Yes, you're right. I'm changing

645
00:29:13,600 --> 00:29:14,990
那我改成三年四个月零十一天
my bet to three years, four months and 11 days.

646
00:29:14,990 --> 00:29:15,570
敢赌吗
A bet?!

647
00:29:15,570 --> 00:29:17,230
我理解你的不赞同 华生
I understand your disapproval, Watson,

648
00:29:17,230 --> 00:29:18,730
但他好胜心切
but if he's feeling competitive,

649
00:29:18,730 --> 00:29:20,570
完全可以自己控制死亡时间
it's perfectly within his power to die early.

650
00:29:21,110 --> 00:29:22,880
这是必须要承担的风险
That's a risk you'll have to take.

651
00:29:22,890 --> 00:29:24,710
你这是在拿自己的性命打赌
You're gambling with your own life?

652
00:29:24,730 --> 00:29:27,310
为何不呢 这比拿别人性命打赌 有意思多了
Why not? It's so much more exciting than gambling with others'.

653
00:29:27,310 --> 00:29:29,570
这块葡萄干布丁下肚 我赌你只能活三年
Three years flat, if you eat that plum pudding!

654
00:29:29,570 --> 00:29:30,480
成交
Done.

655
00:29:36,830 --> 00:29:40,280
前几天的庄园一案 我以为会遇见你
I expected to see you a few days ago about the Manor House case.

656
00:29:40,290 --> 00:29:42,830
我想那案子 你有点力不从心吧
I thought you might be a little out of your depth there.

657
00:29:42,830 --> 00:29:44,330
不会 我已经解决了
No. I solved it.

658
00:29:44,330 --> 00:29:46,910
- 肯定是亚当斯 - 对 是亚当斯
- It was Adams, of course. - Yes, it was Adams.

659
00:29:46,910 --> 00:29:48,120
他是因嫉妒而杀人
Murderous jealousy. He'd

660
00:29:48,130 --> 00:29:50,660
他为皇家天文学会写了一篇
written a paper for the Royal Astronomical Society

661
00:29:50,660 --> 00:29:53,240
关于黄赤交角的论文
on the obliquity of the ecliptic,

662
00:29:53,240 --> 00:29:56,000
然后他又读到一篇 更棒的文章
and then read another that seemed to surpass it.

663
00:29:56,220 --> 00:29:58,320
- 我知道 我看了 - 你看懂了吗
- I know, I read it. - Did you understand it?

664
00:29:58,330 --> 00:30:00,990
我当然能看懂 那文章非常简单
Yes, of course I understood it, it was perfectly simple.

665
00:30:00,990 --> 00:30:03,700
不 你懂嫉妒杀人吗
No, did you understand the murderous jealousy?

666
00:30:03,700 --> 00:30:05,150
让一个聪明人
It is no easy thing for a

667
00:30:05,150 --> 00:30:07,820
去读懂更聪明人的心思 实属不易啊
great mind to contemplate a still greater one.

668
00:30:09,280 --> 00:30:11,910
所以你叫我来 就是为了羞辱我吗
Did you summon me here just to humiliate me?

669
00:30:11,910 --> 00:30:13,360
当然
Yes.

670
00:30:13,370 --> 00:30:15,740
当然不是 但这是我目前最大的乐趣了
Of course not, but it is by far the greater pleasure.

671
00:30:15,740 --> 00:30:17,390
你能否解释下叫我来的原因
Then would you mind explaining exactly why you did summon...?

672
00:30:17,390 --> 00:30:21,360
我们的生活正在被 一位无形的敌人威胁着
Our way of life is under threat from an invisible enemy.

673
00:30:21,360 --> 00:30:24,530
这个人每天都在我们身边徘徊
One that hovers at our elbow on a daily basis.

674
00:30:24,530 --> 00:30:30,780
这些敌人无处不在 悄无声息 无人能挡
These enemies are everywhere... undetected... and unstoppable.

675
00:30:30,780 --> 00:30:32,450
他们是社会主义者吗
Socialists?

676
00:30:32,450 --> 00:30:34,780
不是社会主义者 医生
Not socialists, Doctor, no.

677
00:30:34,780 --> 00:30:36,320
- 他们是无政府主义者吗 - 不是
Anarchists? No.

678
00:30:36,320 --> 00:30:38,860
他们是法国人吗 还是妇女参政者
The French? The suffragists?

679
00:30:38,860 --> 00:30:41,740
还有你没有关心到的 大规模人群吗
Is there any large body of people you're not concerned about?

680
00:30:41,740 --> 00:30:44,530
华生医生永远心怀警惕 你详细说明一下
Dr. Watson is endlessly vigilant. Elaborate...

681
00:30:44,530 --> 00:30:46,240
不 你去调查吧
No. Investigate.

682
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:49,070
这只是我的推测 我需要你去证实它
This is a conjecture of mine, I need you to confirm it.

683
00:30:49,070 --> 00:30:50,650
我把这个案子交给你
I'm sending you a case.

684
00:30:50,650 --> 00:30:52,530
- 他们是苏格兰人吧 - 什么苏格兰人
- The Scots? - The Scots?!

685
00:30:52,530 --> 00:30:54,900
你知道最近有个理论是关于
Are you aware of recent theories concerning what is

686
00:30:54,900 --> 00:30:56,230
妄想症的吗
known as paranoia?

687
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:58,190
这话听着像是塞尔维亚人
Oh, sounds Serbian.

688
00:30:58,190 --> 00:31:00,860
有个叫卡迈克尔的女人 会去找你
A woman will call on you, Lady Carmichael.

689
00:31:00,860 --> 00:31:02,290
我要你接下她的案子
I want you to take her case.

690
00:31:02,290 --> 00:31:04,360
你如果不告诉我们 这些敌人是谁
But these enemies, how are we to defeat them

691
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:06,110
我们要如何打败他们
if you won't tell us about them?

692
00:31:06,110 --> 00:31:09,770
我们无法打败他们 我们永远也无法战胜他们
We don't defeat them. We most certainly lose to them.

693
00:31:10,550 --> 00:31:11,550
为什么
Why?

694
00:31:13,360 --> 00:31:17,030
因为他们是对的 而我们是错的
Because they are right. And we are wrong.

695
00:31:17,820 --> 00:31:19,980
卡迈克尔女士那里 是什么案子
Lady Carmichael's case, what is it?

696
00:31:19,980 --> 00:31:22,860
放心吧 是你会感兴趣的案子
Rest assured, it has features of interest.

697
00:31:22,860 --> 00:31:25,360
- 我从未这么说过 - 你真的说过
I never really say that. You really do.

698
00:31:25,360 --> 00:31:26,600
我估计你已经解决了吧
And you've solved it already, I assume?

699
00:31:26,600 --> 00:31:30,900
只是想通了而已 我要你帮我跑个腿
Only in my head. I need you for the, er, legwork.

700
00:31:30,900 --> 00:31:32,850
为何不告诉我们 你的推理呢
Why not just tell us your solution?

701
00:31:32,860 --> 00:31:35,560
那还有什么意思呢
And where would be the sport in that?

702
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:36,980
你愿意接手这个案子吗 夏洛克
Will you do it, Sherlock?

703
00:31:36,980 --> 00:31:39,330
我保证这会是个极好的消遣
I can promise you a superior distraction.

704
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:41,810
我就一个条件 你再吃个葡萄干布丁吧
On one condition. Have another plum pudding.

705
00:31:41,810 --> 00:31:43,190
我正准备吃呢
There's one on the way.

706
00:31:43,190 --> 00:31:44,810
你只能活两年十一个月零四天了
Two years, 11 months and four days.

707
00:31:44,810 --> 00:31:49,060
开始变得好玩咯 滴答 滴答
Ha, it's getting exciting now! Ticktock, ticktock, ticktock.

708
00:31:53,190 --> 00:31:55,020
谢了 威尔德
Thank you, Wilder.

709
00:31:55,020 --> 00:31:58,270
有一位梅拉斯先生要见你 福尔摩斯先生
Also, a Mr. Melas to see you, Mr. Holmes.

710
00:31:58,270 --> 00:32:01,100
等我五分钟 我还有场赌局要赢呢
Ah. Give me five minutes, I have a wager to win.

711
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:06,770
你还是等我十五分钟吧
Better make that 15.

712
00:32:08,430 --> 00:32:10,230
滴答
Ticktock.

713
00:32:13,880 --> 00:32:16,600
福尔摩斯先生 我是来请你出主意的
Mr. Holmes, I have come here for advice.

714
00:32:16,600 --> 00:32:18,850
- 那倒不难 - 还有您的帮助
- That is easily got. - And help.

715
00:32:18,850 --> 00:32:20,890
那就未必容易了
Not always so easy.

716
00:32:20,890 --> 00:32:24,350
福尔摩斯先生 我遇到了一些 不寻常的事情
Something has happened, Mr. Holmes, something... unusual

717
00:32:24,350 --> 00:32:27,900
骇人听闻的事情
and... terrifying.

718
00:32:27,920 --> 00:32:28,760
那你真是太幸运了
Then you are in luck.

719
00:32:28,770 --> 00:32:30,280
幸运吗
Luck?!

720
00:32:30,280 --> 00:32:33,110
那是我的专长 这个案子有点意思
Those are my specialisms. Hmm, this is really very promising.

721
00:32:33,140 --> 00:32:34,350
福尔摩斯
Holmes...

722
00:32:35,770 --> 00:32:38,810
请告诉我们 您在苦恼些什么
Please... do tell us what has so distressed you.

723
00:32:40,810 --> 00:32:43,720
我思前想后很久 不知该怎么办
I... I thought long and hard as to what to do,

724
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:46,850
后来突然想起 我丈夫与您的哥哥相识
but then it occurred to me that my husband was

725
00:32:46,850 --> 00:32:51,550
所以也许通过他...
an acquaintance of your brother and that perhaps through him...

726
00:32:51,550 --> 00:32:52,730
其实我也不太确定
The fact is, I'm not sure

727
00:32:52,730 --> 00:32:54,760
这事是否在您的管辖范围内 福尔摩斯先生
this comes within your purview, Mr. Holmes.

728
00:32:54,760 --> 00:32:56,010
是吗
No?

729
00:32:56,010 --> 00:32:59,010
上帝啊 也许我该找个驱魔师
Lord help me, I think it may be a matter for a priest.

730
00:33:01,510 --> 00:33:04,470
你早晨受到什么惊吓了 亲爱的
And what does your morning threaten, my dear?

731
00:33:05,890 --> 00:33:08,360
刺绣做地停不下来吗
A vigorous round of embroidering?

732
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:10,610
还是跟女帽商们见面太频繁了
An exhausting appointment at the milliners?

733
00:33:10,640 --> 00:33:12,550
你就喜欢取笑我 尤斯塔斯
I hope you are teasing, Eustace.

734
00:33:23,810 --> 00:33:25,240
怎么了
What is it?

735
00:33:26,110 --> 00:33:27,190
尤斯塔斯
Eustace?

736
00:33:28,760 --> 00:33:30,420
丹尼尔 苏菲 你们去外面玩会
Daniel, Sophie, go out and play.

737
00:33:30,450 --> 00:33:31,710
但是 妈妈
But, Mama...

738
00:33:31,730 --> 00:33:33,560
听话 快去吧
Look, do as I tell you, quickly now.

739
00:33:48,710 --> 00:33:51,460
尤斯塔斯 这是什么东西
Well, Eustace, what does this mean?

740
00:33:55,620 --> 00:33:56,620
死亡
Death.

741
00:33:57,130 --> 00:33:58,130
什么
What?

742
00:33:58,640 --> 00:34:00,020
这意味着死亡
It means death.

743
00:34:04,050 --> 00:34:08,040
没什么 没什么
Er, nothing, it's, er, it's nothing.

744
00:34:08,050 --> 00:34:10,290
我弄错了
I was... mistaken.

745
00:34:10,300 --> 00:34:12,250
亲爱的 你脸色好苍白
My dear, you've gone quite pale.

746
00:34:13,490 --> 00:34:15,030
我没事
It's nothing!

747
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:20,790
- 尤斯塔斯 - 信封你还留着吗
- Eustace... - 'Did you keep the envelope?'

748
00:34:20,790 --> 00:34:23,460
我丈夫销毁了 但上面什么都没有
My husband destroyed it, but it was blank.

749
00:34:23,460 --> 00:34:25,710
没有姓名 没有地址
No name or address of any kind.

750
00:34:25,710 --> 00:34:29,420
尤斯塔斯先生有在美国待过吗
Tell me, has Sir Eustace spent time in America?

751
00:34:29,420 --> 00:34:31,880
- 没有 - 你们结婚之前 也没有吗
- No. - Not even before your marriage?

752
00:34:31,880 --> 00:34:34,830
- 据我所知没有 - 好吧
- Well, not to my knowledge. - Hmm.

753
00:34:34,830 --> 00:34:38,170
请您接着讲 这个令人着迷的故事吧
Pray, continue with your fascinating narrative.

754
00:34:39,540 --> 00:34:42,830
那件事 发生在上周一的清晨
Well, that incident took place last Monday morning.

755
00:34:43,160 --> 00:34:44,410
两天后 也就是周三
It was two days later on

756
00:34:44,410 --> 00:34:46,710
我丈夫第一次看见了她
the Wednesday that my husband first saw her.

757
00:34:47,990 --> 00:34:48,990
看见了谁
Who?

758
00:34:54,080 --> 00:34:55,750
尤斯塔斯
Eustace?

759
00:35:00,750 --> 00:35:03,450
她来找我了 路易莎
She's come for me, Louisa!

760
00:35:03,460 --> 00:35:06,500
天啊 帮帮我 我的罪孽找到我了
Oh, God, help me, my sins have found me out!

761
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:10,280
谁来找你了 尤斯塔斯 你吓到我了
Who's come for you? Eustace, you're frightening me.

762
00:35:10,470 --> 00:35:13,270
看啊 看啊
Well, look, look!

763
00:35:16,590 --> 00:35:18,240
你没看见她吗
Don't you see her?

764
00:35:18,810 --> 00:35:20,350
我什么也没看见
No, I see no-one.

765
00:35:26,290 --> 00:35:28,330
她走了
Gone.

766
00:35:31,620 --> 00:35:34,580
这又是一个 你瞒着我的秘密吗
You keep so many secrets from me, is this another?

767
00:35:34,580 --> 00:35:35,790
你看见了谁
Who have you seen?

768
00:35:37,940 --> 00:35:39,610
是她
It was her!

769
00:35:41,330 --> 00:35:43,370
那个鬼新娘
It was the Bride!

770
00:35:45,370 --> 00:35:47,200
但你什么也没看见吗
And you saw nothing?

771
00:35:47,200 --> 00:35:48,490
是的
Nothing.

772
00:35:48,490 --> 00:35:52,270
- 你丈夫有描述过... - 没有 直到今天早晨
- Did your husband describe...? - Nothing, until this morning.

773
00:36:08,590 --> 00:36:10,300
尤斯塔斯
Eustace?!

774
00:36:23,230 --> 00:36:24,330
尤斯塔斯
Eustace?!

775
00:36:34,370 --> 00:36:35,470
尤斯塔斯 是你吗
Eustace?

776
00:36:39,620 --> 00:36:41,240
尤斯塔斯
Eustace?!

777
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:47,730
该死的
Blast!

778
00:36:47,740 --> 00:36:49,360
尤斯塔斯
Eustace?!

779
00:36:49,360 --> 00:36:51,030
你去哪里了 是我啊
Where are you? It's me!

780
00:36:53,860 --> 00:36:58,610
# 勿忘我 #
Do not forget me

781
00:36:58,610 --> 00:37:03,280
# 勿忘我 #
Do not forget me

782
00:37:04,570 --> 00:37:08,070
# 还记得那少女吗 #
Remember the maid

783
00:37:08,070 --> 00:37:11,690
# 那个磨坊少女 #
The maid of the mill...

784
00:37:26,650 --> 00:37:27,730
你是谁
Who are you?

785
00:37:30,570 --> 00:37:33,070
我命令你 报上名来
I demand you speak, who are you?!

786
00:37:36,370 --> 00:37:40,450
尤斯塔斯 说句话啊 天啊
Eustace, speak to me. In the name of God!

787
00:37:42,870 --> 00:37:43,870
她是...
She's...

788
00:37:44,840 --> 00:37:47,010
她是艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂
She is Emelia Ricoletti.

789
00:37:54,250 --> 00:37:57,450
不 不可能是你
No, not you.

790
00:37:59,390 --> 00:38:00,390
不要
No...

791
00:38:01,600 --> 00:38:03,270
求你了
Please!

792
00:38:03,270 --> 00:38:08,980
今晚 尤斯塔斯·卡迈克尔 你必死无疑
This night, Eustace Carmichael, you will die!

793
00:38:39,160 --> 00:38:40,550
- 福尔摩斯 - 别出声 华生
- Holmes? - Hush, Watson.

794
00:38:40,560 --> 00:38:42,390
艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂 那个新娘
But Emelia Ricoletti, the Bride.

795
00:38:42,390 --> 00:38:45,010
- 你知道她的名字吗 - 请原谅华生
- Well, you know the name? - You must forgive Watson,

796
00:38:45,010 --> 00:38:46,290
他就热衷于说一些
he has an enthusiasm for

797
00:38:46,290 --> 00:38:48,640
显而易见的事实 他就喜欢这样
stating the obvious, which borders on mania.

798
00:38:48,660 --> 00:38:50,640
请问 您丈夫今早还好吗
May I ask, how is your husband this morning?

799
00:38:50,640 --> 00:38:53,010
他拒绝谈论此事
He refuses to speak about the matter.

800
00:38:53,010 --> 00:38:54,990
显然 我已催促 让他离开家
Obviously, I have urged him to leave the house.

801
00:38:55,060 --> 00:38:56,760
不行 他必须得待在家里
No, no, he must stay exactly where he is.

802
00:38:56,760 --> 00:38:58,590
您不觉得 他正处于危险之中吗
Well, you don't think he's in danger?

803
00:38:58,590 --> 00:38:59,510
当然 的确是有人
Oh, no, somebody definitely

804
00:38:59,510 --> 00:39:00,940
想害他性命 但对我们来说是件好事
wants to kill him, but that's good for us.

805
00:39:01,060 --> 00:39:02,800
要设陷阱 还需先有诱饵
You can't set a trap without bait.

806
00:39:03,180 --> 00:39:04,980
我丈夫可不是诱饵 福尔摩斯先生
My husband is not bait, Mr. Holmes.

807
00:39:05,050 --> 00:39:06,610
如果我们确保万无一失 就没有关系
No, but he could be if we play our cards right.

808
00:39:06,640 --> 00:39:09,380
听着 你现在立刻回家
Now, listen, you must go home immediately.

809
00:39:09,390 --> 00:39:11,510
华生医生和我会乘坐下一班火车过去
Dr. Watson and I will follow on the next train.

810
00:39:11,510 --> 00:39:13,570
一刻也不能耽搁 尤斯塔斯爵士今夜会死
There's not a moment to lose, Sir Eustace is to die tonight.

811
00:39:13,600 --> 00:39:14,160
福尔摩斯
Holmes.

812
00:39:14,510 --> 00:39:17,010
我们也许能避免此事
And we should... probably avoid that.

813
00:39:17,010 --> 00:39:19,220
- 是一定 - 一定会避免此事
- Definitely. - Definitely avoid that.

814
00:39:25,220 --> 00:39:29,050
当然 我弟弟接下了这件案子
Little brother has taken the case, of course.

815
00:39:29,050 --> 00:39:31,630
那就拜托你 帮我多留心此事了
I now rely on you to keep an eye on things,

816
00:39:31,630 --> 00:39:34,300
但绝不能让他怀疑 你在为我办事
but he must never suspect you are working for me.

817
00:39:34,300 --> 00:39:36,380
听清楚了吗 华生
Are you clear on that, Watson?

818
00:39:40,050 --> 00:39:42,090
请相信我 福尔摩斯先生
You can rely on me, Mr. Holmes.

819
00:39:46,490 --> 00:39:48,250
- 你说会不会 - 不会 你也不该有这种想法
You don't suppose... - I don't and neither should you.

820
00:39:48,260 --> 00:39:49,960
你又不知道我打算说什么
You don't know what I was going to say.

821
00:39:49,960 --> 00:39:51,970
你是想说 可能有什么超自然的力量
You were about to suggest there may be some supernatural agency

822
00:39:51,970 --> 00:39:54,730
牵扯其中 而我正准备当面嘲笑你
involved in this matter. And I was about to laugh in your face.

823
00:39:54,760 --> 00:39:57,880
但那个新娘 艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂再次出现了
But the Bride, Holmes, Emelia Ricoletti again.

824
00:39:57,880 --> 00:39:59,410
一名死去的女子又重现人间
A dead woman walking the earth.

825
00:39:59,520 --> 00:40:02,310
- 你真让我惊讶啊 华生 - 是吗
- You amaze me, Watson. - I do?

826
00:40:02,320 --> 00:40:05,940
你什么时候开始 居然这么有想象力了
Since when have you had any kind of imagination?

827
00:40:05,940 --> 00:40:08,230
估计自从我让读者们相信
Perhaps since I convinced the reading public that

828
00:40:08,230 --> 00:40:09,970
道德败坏的瘾君子
an unprincipled drug addict

829
00:40:09,970 --> 00:40:11,150
也能是风度翩翩的英雄人物吧
was some kind of gentleman hero.

830
00:40:11,150 --> 00:40:14,350
是啊 提到这事 你还真是了不起啊
Yes, now you come to mention it, that was quite impressive.

831
00:40:14,360 --> 00:40:18,230
你放心 这个世界上没有鬼
You may, however, rest assured there are no ghosts in this world.

832
00:40:21,940 --> 00:40:24,310
鬼怪只来自我们心中
Save those we make for ourselves.

833
00:40:25,810 --> 00:40:28,390
抱歉 你这话是什么意思
Sorry, what did you say?

834
00:40:29,280 --> 00:40:32,650
我们想象出的鬼 这是什么意思
Ghosts we make for ourselves, what do you mean?

835
00:40:37,480 --> 00:40:38,720
我有梦游症
Somnambulism.

836
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:40,550
您说什么
I beg your pardon?

837
00:40:41,360 --> 00:40:45,110
我会梦游 就这样 不是什么大事
I sleepwalk, that's all. It's a common enough condition.

838
00:40:45,110 --> 00:40:46,940
您不就是医生吗
I thought you were a doctor!

839
00:40:46,940 --> 00:40:50,190
整件事就是一场恶梦
The whole thing was a... bad dream.

840
00:40:50,190 --> 00:40:52,870
包括您收到的 信封里的东西吗
Including the contents of the envelope you received?

841
00:40:53,170 --> 00:40:55,210
那只是个奇怪的玩笑
Well, that's a grotesque joke.

842
00:40:55,310 --> 00:40:58,230
您妻子感觉并非如此啊 先生
Well, that's not the impression you gave your wife, sir.

843
00:40:58,230 --> 00:41:01,650
- 她有臆想病 很容易幻想 - 并非如此
- She's an hysteric, prone to fancies. - No.

844
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:06,900
