- I'm sorry, what did you say? - I said no, she's not an hysteric.

845
00:41:06,900 --> 00:41:09,790
她是个有着罕见洞察力的聪明女人
She's a highly intelligent woman of rare perception.

846
00:41:10,480 --> 00:41:13,350
我的妻子从橙核里看出了恐惧
My wife sees terror in an orange pip.

847
00:41:13,350 --> 00:41:15,600
你的妻子能在别人认为毫无价值的地方
Your wife can see worlds where no-one else can see

848
00:41:15,600 --> 00:41:17,350
看出很多东西
anything of value whatsoever.

849
00:41:17,350 --> 00:41:19,640
真的吗
Can she really?

850
00:41:19,640 --> 00:41:22,850
那您是如何"推理"出来的呢 福尔摩斯先生
And how do you "Deduce" That, Mr. Holmes?

851
00:41:22,850 --> 00:41:24,350
她嫁给了你
She married you.

852
00:41:24,350 --> 00:41:27,390
我想她一定有合理的理由
I assume she was capable of finding a reason.

853
00:41:27,390 --> 00:41:30,060
今晚我会竭尽全力护你周全 但首先
I'll do my best to save your life tonight, but first it would

854
00:41:30,060 --> 00:41:31,270
如果您能解释与瑞克莱蒂一案的关系
help if you would explain your connection.

855
00:41:31,270 --> 00:41:34,140
我想定会大有帮助
to the Ricoletti case.

856
00:41:34,140 --> 00:41:35,810
瑞克莱蒂
Ricoletti?

857
00:41:35,810 --> 00:41:38,390
是的 请详情说来
Yes. In detail, please.

858
00:41:38,390 --> 00:41:40,140
我从未听说过她
I've never heard of her.

859
00:41:40,140 --> 00:41:42,560
有意思 我并没有提到 她是个女人
Interesting. I didn't mention she was a woman.

860
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:45,770
我们先告辞了 希望明早还能再见到你
We'll show ourselves out. I hope to see you again in the morning.

861
00:41:45,770 --> 00:41:47,040
我们不会再见面了
You will not.

862
00:41:47,120 --> 00:41:50,080
那可真是不幸 那我就得来破你的谋杀案了 再会
Then sadly I shall be solving your murder. Good day.

863
00:41:55,870 --> 00:41:57,460
你尽力了
Well, you tried.

864
00:41:59,040 --> 00:42:01,180
请转交给卡迈克尔夫人 谢谢
Will you see that Lady Carmichael receives this. Thank you.

865
00:42:01,210 --> 00:42:02,610
- 午安 - 没问题 先生
- Good afternoon. - Certainly, sir.

866
00:42:03,680 --> 00:42:04,680
那是什么
What was that?

867
00:42:04,700 --> 00:42:06,040
卡迈克尔夫人今晚
Lady Carmichael will sleep alone tonight,

868
00:42:06,040 --> 00:42:07,950
会假装头痛难忍 而独自就寝
upon the pretence of a violent headache.

869
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:10,500
所有的门窗都会上锁
All the doors and windows of the house will be locked.

870
00:42:10,500 --> 00:42:15,500
你觉得那幽灵 那鬼新娘
Ha! You think the spectre, er, Bride,

871
00:42:15,500 --> 00:42:18,120
会再次试图将尤斯塔斯爵士 引到外面去吗
will attempt to lure Sir Eustace outside again?

872
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:20,540
当然 不然她为何口出狂言
Certainly. Why else the portentous threat?

873
00:42:20,540 --> 00:42:23,790
- "今晚你必死无疑" - 他不会跟出去的吧
- "This night you will die!" - Well, he won't follow her, surely?

874
00:42:23,790 --> 00:42:26,580
他会怎么做 还真的很难说
Hmm, it's difficult to say quite what he'll do.

875
00:42:26,580 --> 00:42:29,450
- 愧疚在吞噬他的灵魂 - 愧疚 什么愧疚
- Guilt is eating away at his soul. - Guilt? About what?

876
00:42:29,450 --> 00:42:31,950
他的过去 那些橙核是个提醒
Something in his past. The orange pips were a reminder.

877
00:42:31,950 --> 00:42:34,070
- 不是玩笑吗 - 完全不是
- Not a joke? - Not at all.

878
00:42:34,140 --> 00:42:35,510
有一个传统是用橙核
Orange pips are a traditional

879
00:42:35,520 --> 00:42:37,890
来预警复仇偿命的 这个起源于美国
warning of avenging death, originating in America.

880
00:42:38,200 --> 00:42:40,490
尤斯塔斯爵士对此再了解不过了
Sir Eustace knows this only too well,

881
00:42:40,490 --> 00:42:42,870
他很清楚自己 为何要受惩罚
just as he knows why he is to be punished.

882
00:42:42,870 --> 00:42:45,080
是和艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂有关吗
Something to do with Emelia Ricoletti?

883
00:42:45,080 --> 00:42:48,910
我想是的 我们都有过去 华生 而鬼魂
I presume. We all have a past, Watson. Ghosts.

884
00:42:48,910 --> 00:42:52,320
他们如同阴霾 正是因为有了阴霾 才会出现阳光
They are the shadows that define our every sunny day.

885
00:42:52,330 --> 00:42:54,240
尤斯塔斯爵士知道自己是逃不过了
Sir Eustace knows he's a marked man.

886
00:42:54,240 --> 00:42:57,160
他恐惧的不仅仅是死亡
There's something more than murder he fears.

887
00:42:57,160 --> 00:43:00,530
他深信死去的瑞克莱蒂太太复活的尸体
He believes he is to be dragged to hell by the risen corpse

888
00:43:00,530 --> 00:43:02,120
会将他拖入万丈深渊
of the late Mrs. Ricoletti.

889
00:43:05,630 --> 00:43:07,260
那也太荒谬了吧
That's a lot of nonsense, isn't it?

890
00:43:07,260 --> 00:43:09,010
老天 当然荒谬了 你的左轮手枪带了吗
God, yes. Did you bring your revolver?

891
00:43:09,010 --> 00:43:10,370
用手枪对付幽灵有用吗
What good would that be against a ghost?

892
00:43:10,400 --> 00:43:12,140
- 那当然 你带了吗 - 嗯 带了
- Exactly. Did you bring it? - Yeah, of course.

893
00:43:12,170 --> 00:43:15,250
那就来吧 华生 来吧 游戏开始了
Then come, Watson, come. The game is afoot.

894
00:43:25,250 --> 00:43:28,430
- 蹲下来 华生 老天啊 - 抱歉 我抽筋了
- Get down, Watson, for heaven's sake! - Sorry. Cramp.

895
00:43:32,040 --> 00:43:34,450
- 灯还亮着吗 - 是的
- Is the lamp still burning? - Yes.

896
00:43:37,690 --> 00:43:39,300
尤斯塔斯爵士的灯灭了
There goes Sir Eustace.

897
00:43:41,480 --> 00:43:42,730
卡迈克尔夫人的灯也灭了
And Lady Carmichael.

898
00:43:43,950 --> 00:43:45,970
整栋房子都入睡了
The house sleeps.

899
00:43:49,090 --> 00:43:51,600
天啊 这是我这一生之中 最漫长的一夜了
Hmm, good God, this is the longest night of my life.

900
00:43:51,600 --> 00:43:53,390
耐心点 华生
Have patience, Watson.

901
00:43:55,390 --> 00:43:56,930
就到午夜而已
Only midnight.

902
00:43:58,770 --> 00:44:02,560
我们很少像现在这样坐在一起
You know, it's rare for us to sit together like this.

903
00:44:02,560 --> 00:44:05,310
我觉得也是 但现在谋杀案迫在眉睫
I should hope so. It's murder on the knees.

904
00:44:06,810 --> 00:44:10,680
两个老朋友说说话 聊聊天
Two old friends just talking. Chewing the fat.

905
00:44:12,240 --> 00:44:13,450
男人和男人之间的对话
Man-to-man.

906
00:44:18,970 --> 00:44:20,550
那个不同寻常的女人
So, a remarkable woman.

907
00:44:20,560 --> 00:44:22,800
- 谁 - 卡迈克尔夫人
- Who? - Lady Carmichael.

908
00:44:22,810 --> 00:44:24,520
女性方面可是你的专长 华生
The fair sex is your department, Watson.

909
00:44:24,540 --> 00:44:25,760
我接受你的评价
I'll take your word for it.

910
00:44:25,780 --> 00:44:28,280
你挺喜欢她的 "那个女人有罕见的洞察力"
Well, you liked her. "A woman of rare perception."

911
00:44:28,720 --> 00:44:29,990
和令人赞叹的高足弓
And admirably high arches.

912
00:44:29,990 --> 00:44:32,260
她一踏进房间我就注意到了
I noticed them as soon as she stepped into the room.

913
00:44:32,260 --> 00:44:34,550
- 他根本配不上她 - 你这么认为吗
- Huh, she's far too good for him. - You think so?

914
00:44:34,550 --> 00:44:36,180
不 是你这么认为 我能看出来
No. You think so. I could tell.

915
00:44:36,180 --> 00:44:37,940
相反 我对此事一点都不在意
On the contrary, I have no view on the matter.

916
00:44:37,970 --> 00:44:39,670
你就是在意
Yes, you have.

917
00:44:41,470 --> 00:44:44,550
- 婚姻不是我会想的东西 - 为什么
- Marriage is not a subject upon which I dwell. - Oh, why not?

918
00:44:44,550 --> 00:44:45,660
你今晚是怎么了
What's the matter with you this evening?

919
00:44:45,740 --> 00:44:48,910
你戴着的那个怀表 里面有一张照片
That watch that you're wearing, there's a photograph inside it.

920
00:44:48,910 --> 00:44:52,680
我有一次瞥见了 我想那是艾琳·艾德勒的照片
I glimpsed it once. I believe it is of Irene Adler.

921
00:44:52,710 --> 00:44:54,860
你才不是瞥见的 你是等我睡着之后
You didn't glimpse it, you waited till I'd fallen asleep

922
00:44:54,870 --> 00:44:56,280
- 自己偷看的 - 是的
- and looked at it. - Yes, I did.

923
00:44:56,280 --> 00:44:59,670
- 你真以为我没注意到吗 - 艾琳·艾德勒
- You seriously thought I wouldn't notice? - Irene Adler.

924
00:45:00,190 --> 00:45:02,090
一个强大的对手 一次难忘的冒险经历
Formidable opponent, a remarkable adventure.

925
00:45:02,120 --> 00:45:04,530
- 那照片很好看 - 你说这些干什么
- A very nice photograph. - Why are you talking like this?

926
00:45:04,530 --> 00:45:06,200
你为何立志要孤身一人
Why are you so determined to be alone?

927
00:45:06,200 --> 00:45:07,100
你还好吧 华生
Are you quite well, Watson?

928
00:45:07,100 --> 00:45:08,340
这是个奇怪的问题吗
Is it such a curious question?

929
00:45:08,340 --> 00:45:10,400
对一个维也纳的精神病医生来说 不是
From a Viennese alienist, no.

930
00:45:10,410 --> 00:45:12,520
但对一个退役军医来说 当然是
From a retired Army surgeon, most certainly.

931
00:45:12,600 --> 00:45:16,100
福尔摩斯 我绝非是你的对手
Holmes, against absolutely no opposition whatsoever,

932
00:45:16,530 --> 00:45:19,570
- 我是你最亲近的朋友 - 我承认
- I am your closest friend. - I concede it.

933
00:45:19,570 --> 00:45:21,320
我现在只是尝试跟你进行一段
I am currently attempting to have

934
00:45:21,320 --> 00:45:23,610
非常正常的对话而已
a perfectly normal conversation with you.

935
00:45:23,610 --> 00:45:27,120
- 求你别了 - 你为什么非得一个人呢
- Please don't. - Why do you need to be alone?

936
00:45:27,530 --> 00:45:30,110
如果你说的是 关于情感纠葛的事 华生
If you are referring to romantic entanglement, Watson,

937
00:45:30,110 --> 00:45:32,420
恐怕你说的就是这个 就像我以前经常解释的那样
which I rather fear you are, as I have often explained before,

938
00:45:32,450 --> 00:45:34,540
我讨厌所有的情感
all emotion is abhorrent to me.

939
00:45:34,970 --> 00:45:37,400
情感是精密仪器上的沙粒
It is the grit in a sensitive instrument.

940
00:45:37,400 --> 00:45:39,560
- 镜头上的裂缝 - 镜头上的裂缝 是的
- The crack in the lens. - The crack in the lens. Yes.

941
00:45:39,720 --> 00:45:41,840
明白了吧 我之前告诉过你
Well, there you are, you see, I've said it all before.

942
00:45:41,870 --> 00:45:43,090
不 这些都是我写的
No, I wrote all that.

943
00:45:43,120 --> 00:45:45,240
你在引用"斯特兰德杂志"里自己的话
You're quoting yourself from The Strand Magazine.

944
00:45:45,320 --> 00:45:48,700
- 正是 - 那是我写的 不是你说的
- Well, exactly. - Those are my words, not yours!

945
00:45:48,700 --> 00:45:52,030
那是我向公众呈现的 你的样子
That is the version of you that I present to the public.

946
00:45:52,030 --> 00:45:55,240
没有情感的头脑 就像一台计算机
The brain without a heart. The calculating machine.

947
00:45:55,240 --> 00:45:58,750
那些都是我写的 福尔摩斯 读者也欣然接受了
I write all of that, Holmes, and the readers lap it up.

948
00:45:58,780 --> 00:46:00,000
但我并不相信这个事实
But I do not believe it.

949
00:46:00,030 --> 00:46:01,550
我想给你的编辑写信
Well, I've a good mind to write to your editor.

950
00:46:01,570 --> 00:46:03,200
你是一个活生生的人
You are a living, breathing man.

951
00:46:03,200 --> 00:46:05,740
- 你有自己的生活 也有过去 - 有什么
- You've lived a life, you have a past. - A what?!

952
00:46:05,740 --> 00:46:08,110
- 你肯定有过... - 有过什么
- Well, you must have had... - Had what?

953
00:46:09,920 --> 00:46:11,330
- 你知道的 - 不知道
- You know. - No.

954
00:46:12,740 --> 00:46:14,450
经历
Experiences.

955
00:46:14,450 --> 00:46:17,110
把你的左轮手枪给我 我突然想用一下
Pass me your revolver, I have a sudden need to use it.

956
00:46:17,110 --> 00:46:19,170
可恶 福尔摩斯 你是血肉之躯
Damn it, Holmes, you are flesh and blood,

957
00:46:19,170 --> 00:46:20,670
你有感觉 你有...
you have feelings, you have...

958
00:46:20,770 --> 00:46:23,920
你肯定会有 冲动
You must have... impulses.

959
00:46:23,990 --> 00:46:25,380
我的天啊 我从来没有像这样
Dear Lord, I have never been

960
00:46:25,380 --> 00:46:27,830
想马上被杀人厉鬼袭击的感觉
so impatient to be attacked by a murderous ghost.

961
00:46:27,850 --> 00:46:32,370
作为你的朋友 作为一个担心你的人
As your friend, as someone who worries about you...

962
00:46:34,130 --> 00:46:36,010
是什么事情 造就了你性格
What made you like this?

963
00:46:37,640 --> 00:46:39,100
华生
Oh, Watson...

964
00:46:41,040 --> 00:46:42,490
无事造就了我
Nothing made me.

965
00:46:45,080 --> 00:46:46,540
我造就了自己
I made me.

966
00:46:48,450 --> 00:46:49,450
红胡子
Redbeard?

967
00:46:49,700 --> 00:46:51,410
我的天啊
Good God!

968
00:46:57,960 --> 00:46:59,030
我们该怎么办
What are we to do?

969
00:47:04,000 --> 00:47:05,870
我们去跟她聊会天吧
Why don't we have a chat?

970
00:47:12,690 --> 00:47:14,900
我想你是瑞克莱蒂夫人吧
Mrs. Ricoletti, I believe!

971
00:47:14,900 --> 00:47:17,520
每年的今晚 真是宜人 对吧
A pleasant night for the time of year, is it not?

972
00:47:17,520 --> 00:47:19,900
这不可能是真的 福尔摩斯 这不可能
It cannot be true, Holmes, it cannot!

973
00:47:19,900 --> 00:47:22,310
对 不可能
No, it can't.

974
00:47:30,940 --> 00:47:33,150
- 门锁上了吗 - 按要求锁着呢
- Is it locked? - As per instruction.

975
00:47:33,150 --> 00:47:35,150
那是打破窗户的声音吗
That was a window breaking, wasn't it?

976
00:47:35,150 --> 00:47:37,630
我们只用担心 一扇打破的窗户就行了
There's only one broken window we need concern ourselves with.

977
00:47:48,570 --> 00:47:50,070
- 待在这里 华生 - 什么 我不要
- Stay here, Watson. - What? No.

978
00:47:50,070 --> 00:47:52,490
房子里所有的窗户 和门都上了锁
All the doors and windows to the house are locked.

979
00:47:52,490 --> 00:47:54,570
这是他们唯一的出口 我需要你在这守着
This is their only way out, I need you here!

980
00:47:54,590 --> 00:47:55,470
但那个声音那么近
But the sound was so close.

981
00:47:55,470 --> 00:47:56,800
肯定是从房子这边传来的
It had to be from this side of the house.

982
00:47:56,820 --> 00:47:57,820
待在这里
Stay here!

983
00:48:12,860 --> 00:48:14,320
不
No!

984
00:48:22,440 --> 00:48:25,280
你保证会护他安全 你保证过的
You promised to keep him safe. You promised!

985
00:48:26,010 --> 00:48:27,640
你
You...

986
00:48:51,930 --> 00:48:53,520
你是人 我知道
You're human, I know that.

987
00:48:57,090 --> 00:48:58,090
你肯定是人
You must be.

988
00:49:02,600 --> 00:49:06,560
我们站在黑暗中也没用
Little use us standing here in the dark.

989
00:49:08,140 --> 00:49:11,930
毕竟 这是十九世纪了
After all, this is the 19th century.

990
00:49:54,590 --> 00:49:58,050
勿忘我
Do not forget me!

991
00:49:59,300 --> 00:50:02,880
勿忘我
Do not forget me!

992
00:50:10,610 --> 00:50:11,610
华生
Watson!

993
00:50:11,630 --> 00:50:12,880
她在那里 她就在那里
She's there! She's down there!

994
00:50:12,880 --> 00:50:14,550
别告诉我 你擅离职守了
Don't tell me you abandoned your post!

995
00:50:14,580 --> 00:50:16,450
什么 福尔摩斯 她就在那里 我看见她了
What? Holmes, she's there, I saw her!

996
00:50:20,950 --> 00:50:22,910
没人 这都得感谢你
Empty, thanks to you!

997
00:50:23,130 --> 00:50:24,360
我们的目标跑了
Our bird is flown!

998
00:50:24,380 --> 00:50:27,250
不 福尔摩斯 不是你想的那样
No! No, Holmes, it wasn't what you think.

999
00:50:27,270 --> 00:50:28,670
我看见她了 那个鬼魂
I saw her! The ghost!

1000
00:50:28,700 --> 00:50:31,050
世界上 没有 鬼魂
There are no ghosts!

1001
00:50:34,790 --> 00:50:37,860
那发生什么事了 尤斯塔斯先生在哪里
What happened? Where is Sir Eustace?

1002
00:50:40,250 --> 00:50:41,630
他死了
Dead.

1003
00:50:45,090 --> 00:50:47,110
你不需要责怪自己
You really mustn't blame yourself, you know.

1004
00:50:47,180 --> 00:50:51,490
- 你说得对 - 很高兴你终于明事理了
- No, you're quite right. - I'm glad you're seeing sense.

1005
00:50:51,520 --> 00:50:52,920
华生也该受罚
Watson is equally culpable.

1006
00:50:52,920 --> 00:50:55,420
我们已经设法 搞砸了整个案子
Between us, we've managed to botch this whole case.

1007
00:50:55,420 --> 00:50:57,420
我承诺过要保护那个男人
I gave an undertaking to protect that man,

1008
00:50:57,420 --> 00:50:59,710
但他现在躺在那里 胸口上还插着把匕首
now he's lying there with a dagger in his breast.

1009
00:50:59,710 --> 00:51:01,660
事实上 你只是承诺过 要调查他的谋杀案
In fact, you gave an undertaking to investigate his murder.

1010
00:51:01,690 --> 00:51:04,110
因为我非常相信 他一定不会死
In the confident expectation I would not have to!

1011
00:51:06,860 --> 00:51:08,320
你发现什么了吗 医生
Anything you can tell us, Doctor?

1012
00:51:08,830 --> 00:51:12,710
捅他的人力气可不小
Well, he's been stabbed with considerable force.

1013
00:51:12,710 --> 00:51:15,960
- 凶手是个男人吗 - 有可能
- It's a man, then? - Possibly.

1014
00:51:15,960 --> 00:51:18,910
刀刃非常锋利 所以也有可能是个女人吧
A very keen blade, so it could conceivably have been a woman?

1015
00:51:18,920 --> 00:51:21,620
理论上来说 是的 但我们知道是谁 我看见她了
In theory, yes, but we know who it was, I saw her.

1016
00:51:22,600 --> 00:51:24,060
- 华生 - 我亲眼看见那个鬼魂了
- Watson! - I saw the ghost, with my own eyes!

1017
00:51:24,060 --> 00:51:24,770
你看到的都是假象
You saw nothing!

1018
00:51:24,770 --> 00:51:26,160
是他们想要你 看见那个鬼魂
You saw what you were supposed to see!

1019
00:51:26,160 --> 00:51:28,160
你自己也说过 我没有想象力
You said yourself, I have no imagination.

1020
00:51:28,160 --> 00:51:28,970
那你就动脑啊 尽管没什么用
Then use your brain, such as it is,

1021
00:51:28,970 --> 00:51:30,220
至少能排除掉不可能的因素
to eliminate the impossible,

1022
00:51:30,240 --> 00:51:31,480
在这桩案件中 鬼魂就是不可能因素
which in this case is the ghost,

1023
00:51:31,480 --> 00:51:32,840
然后再观察其它的线索
and observe what remains,

1024
00:51:32,840 --> 00:51:34,200
这桩案子的谜底
which in this case is a solution

1025
00:51:34,230 --> 00:51:36,410
已经明显到 连莱斯特雷德都能看出来了
so blindingly obvious even Lestrade could work it out!

1026
00:51:36,490 --> 00:51:37,490
谢谢夸奖
Thank you!

1027
00:51:37,520 --> 00:51:39,910
别去想另一个世界的幽灵了
Forget spectres from the other world!

1028
00:51:39,910 --> 00:51:42,660
只有一个嫌疑人有动机 也有机会
There is only one suspect with motive and opportunity.

1029
00:51:42,660 --> 00:51:45,160
- 他们可能又留了字条 - 他们确实留了字条
- They might as well have left a note. - They did leave a note.

1030
00:51:45,160 --> 00:51:47,620
还有另一扇破窗户的问题
And then there's the matter of the other broken window.

1031
00:51:47,620 --> 00:51:50,080
- 什么另一扇破窗户 - 正是 没有另一扇
- What other broken window? - Precisely! There isn't one.

1032
00:51:50,080 --> 00:51:51,340
唯一被打破的窗户
The only broken window is

1033
00:51:51,340 --> 00:51:53,450
就是我和华生进来的那扇
the one that Watson and I entered through,

1034
00:51:53,450 --> 00:51:55,360
但在那之前 我们清晰地听到了声音
yet, prior to that, we distinctly heard the sound of...

1035
00:51:55,390 --> 00:51:56,800
- 你刚说了什么 - 什么
- What did you just say? - Sorry?

1036
00:51:57,320 --> 00:51:58,760
关于字条的事 你刚说了什么
About a note, what did you just say?

1037
00:51:58,790 --> 00:52:01,580
- 我说凶手确实留了张字条 - 不 他们没留
- I said the murderer DID leave a note. - No, they didn't.

1038
00:52:01,580 --> 00:52:04,530
匕首上绑了一张字条 你看定看见了
There's a message tied to the dagger. You must have seen it!

1039
00:52:04,540 --> 00:52:06,280
- 根本没有字条 - 有的
- There's no message. - Yes!

1040
00:52:06,280 --> 00:52:08,780
我发现尸体的时候 根本没有字条
There was no message when I found the body.

1041
00:52:25,240 --> 00:52:26,620
福尔摩斯
Holmes?

1042
00:52:30,410 --> 00:52:31,740
上面写了什么
What is it?

1043
00:52:51,400 --> 00:52:53,070
你想吗
Do you?

1044
00:52:53,070 --> 00:52:54,490
想什么
Do I what?

1045
00:52:57,820 --> 00:52:59,990
你怎么拿到这个的
H... how did you get that?

1046
00:52:59,990 --> 00:53:02,690
我把它留在犯罪现场了
I left it at the crime scene.

1047
00:53:02,690 --> 00:53:04,050
