her mouth and shot the back of her head off

1150
01:00:25,890 --> 01:00:27,260
但她却又起死回生了
and then she came back.

1151
01:00:29,140 --> 01:00:32,680
不可能的事 但她做到了
Impossible. But she did it.

1152
01:00:32,690 --> 01:00:34,480
你想知道她是怎么做到的
And you need to know how.

1153
01:00:35,400 --> 01:00:36,600
这究竟是怎么回事
How?

1154
01:00:36,650 --> 01:00:37,650
是不是
Don't you?

1155
01:00:37,980 --> 01:00:40,320
因为这个谜团 你的世界都要分崩离析了
It's tearing your world apart, not knowing.

1156
01:00:40,320 --> 01:00:46,240
你是想阻止我 让我分心 让我脱离正轨
You're trying to stop me... To distract me, derail me.

1157
01:00:46,260 --> 01:00:48,410
因为这让你想起了另一个案子吧
Because doesn't this remind you of another case?

1158
01:00:49,560 --> 01:00:51,970
这一切以前都发生过吧
Hasn't this all happened before?

1159
01:00:52,000 --> 01:00:54,580
天下原无新鲜事 以前发生过什么事情
There's nothing new under the sun. What was it?

1160
01:00:55,050 --> 01:00:58,720
是什么事情 是什么案子
What was it? What was that case? Huh?

1161
01:00:58,720 --> 01:01:00,260
你记得吗
Do you remember?

1162
01:01:01,570 --> 01:01:04,670
就在我嘴边了 我要说出来了
It's on the tip of my tongue. It's on the tip of my tongue.

1163
01:01:04,690 --> 01:01:06,380
我马上就要说出来了
It's on the tip of my tongue.

1164
01:01:07,400 --> 01:01:08,980
就在
It's on the tip...

1165
01:01:14,040 --> 01:01:15,500
我舌头上了
of my tongue.

1166
01:01:19,950 --> 01:01:22,490
为了哈德森夫人的墙纸着想 我得提醒你
For the sake of Mrs. Hudson's wallpaper, I must remind you

1167
01:01:22,500 --> 01:01:25,330
你的手指乱动一下 你就会死
that one false move with your finger and you will be dead.

1168
01:01:25,330 --> 01:01:28,450
你说什么
I'm sorry?

1169
01:01:30,660 --> 01:01:34,640
死亡 是新的性感体验
Dead... is the new sexy.

1170
01:01:44,160 --> 01:01:47,870
这一枪把我彻底打醒了
Well, I'll tell you what, that rather blows the cobwebs away.

1171
01:01:47,870 --> 01:01:50,550
- 你怎么可能还活着 - 我看起来怎么样
- How can you be alive? - How do I look?

1172
01:01:57,620 --> 01:01:59,830
你跟我说实话 这很显眼是吧
You can be honest, is it noticeable?

1173
01:01:59,830 --> 01:02:03,200
你打穿了自己的大脑 怎么可能还活着
You blew your own brains out, how could you survive?

1174
01:02:03,200 --> 01:02:04,660
我梳个背头 应该能挡住
Or maybe I could backcomb.

1175
01:02:04,660 --> 01:02:05,990
我亲眼看到你死了
I saw you die.

1176
01:02:08,180 --> 01:02:09,970
你为什么还没死
Why aren't you dead?

1177
01:02:10,230 --> 01:02:13,200
因为不是瀑布害死了你 夏洛克
Because it's not the fall that kills you, Sherlock.

1178
01:02:14,230 --> 01:02:17,640
你比所有人都清楚 不是瀑布
Of all people, you should know that, it's not the fall,

1179
01:02:17,640 --> 01:02:19,730
瀑布不会害死你
it's never the fall.

1180
01:02:21,940 --> 01:02:23,490
你是在降落了
It's the landing!

1181
01:02:39,960 --> 01:02:42,660
我们着陆了 先生 我们已经着陆了
We've landed, sir. We've landed.

1182
01:02:43,650 --> 01:02:45,650
别 别现在叫醒我
No, no, not now, not now!

1183
01:02:49,220 --> 01:02:50,680
别现在醒来啊
Not now, not now.

1184
01:02:50,680 --> 01:02:52,510
我相信您 度过了个愉快的航程 先生
I trust you had a pleasant flight, sir?

1185
01:02:52,510 --> 01:02:55,790
这流放比我们想得还要短 我的弟弟
Well, a somewhat shorter exile than we'd imagined, brother mine,

1186
01:02:55,930 --> 01:02:58,140
不过你作为重度强迫症患者 大概也足够长了
but probably adequate, given your levels of OCD.

1187
01:02:58,140 --> 01:02:59,390
- 我得回去 - 什么
- I have to go back! - What?

1188
01:02:59,390 --> 01:03:01,340
我 我就快明白了 我马上就知道了
I was... I was nearly there, I nearly had it!

1189
01:03:01,340 --> 01:03:03,010
你到底在说什么东西
What on earth are you talking about?

1190
01:03:03,010 --> 01:03:05,120
回哪里去 你没飞多远啊
Go back where? You didn't get very far.

1191
01:03:05,150 --> 01:03:08,020
瑞克莱蒂和他可恶的妻子 你们懂了吗
Ricoletti and his abominable wife! Don't you understand?!

1192
01:03:08,030 --> 01:03:10,280
不 我们当然不懂 你在说胡话呢 夏洛克
No, of course we don't, you're not making any sense, Sherlock.

1193
01:03:10,430 --> 01:03:13,840
那是一个一百年前的名案
It was a case, a famous one from 100 years ago.

1194
01:03:13,840 --> 01:03:15,000
存在我的硬盘里
Lodged in my hard drive,

1195
01:03:15,000 --> 01:03:17,220
她本应该死了 却又死而复生
she seemed to be dead, but then she came back.

1196
01:03:17,220 --> 01:03:18,390
什么 像莫里亚蒂一样吗
What, like Moriarty?

1197
01:03:18,410 --> 01:03:20,360
朝着头开了一枪 跟莫里亚蒂一模一样
Shot herself in the head, exactly like Moriarty.

1198
01:03:20,510 --> 01:03:21,750
但是你才刚刚知道
But you've only just been told.

1199
01:03:21,770 --> 01:03:23,020
我们也是刚刚才知道
We've only just found out,

1200
01:03:23,020 --> 01:03:24,890
他出现在了全国所有的电视屏幕上
he's on every TV screen in the country.

1201
01:03:25,130 --> 01:03:27,860
所以呢 迈克罗夫特的电话 都已经打来五分钟了
Yes? So? It's been five minutes since Mycroft called.

1202
01:03:27,890 --> 01:03:30,050
你们有什么进展 你们做了什么事情
What progress have you made? What have you been doing?

1203
01:03:30,050 --> 01:03:31,960
更重要的是 你又做了什么事情
More to the point, what have YOU been doing?

1204
01:03:31,970 --> 01:03:33,340
我当然一直在思维殿堂里
I've been in my Mind Palace, of course.

1205
01:03:33,370 --> 01:03:33,680
当然了
Of course.

1206
01:03:33,710 --> 01:03:35,560
做一个实验 如果我在1895年的现场
Running an experiment. How would I have solved the crime,

1207
01:03:35,590 --> 01:03:39,760
- 我会怎么破这个案 - 夏洛克
- if I'd been there in 1895? - Oh, Sherlock.

1208
01:03:39,930 --> 01:03:42,220
我掌握了所有的细节
I had all the details perfect.

1209
01:03:42,220 --> 01:03:44,510
我就在现场 万事俱备 我正沉浸其中
I was there, all of it, everything. I was immersed.

1210
01:03:44,510 --> 01:03:45,760
是啊 正是如此
Of course you were.

1211
01:03:45,760 --> 01:03:48,440
你一直在读约翰的博客 你们相遇的故事
You've been reading John's blog. The story of how you met.

1212
01:03:49,450 --> 01:03:51,840
有些时候通过他的视角 审视自己很有帮助
It helps me if I see myself through his eyes sometimes.

1213
01:03:51,850 --> 01:03:53,220
我比他聪明多了
I'm so much cleverer.

1214
01:03:54,300 --> 01:03:56,300
你觉得有谁 会相信你的话吗
Do you really think anyone is believing you?

1215
01:03:56,300 --> 01:03:57,720
不 他能做到 我见过的
No, he can do this, I've seen it.

1216
01:03:57,720 --> 01:04:00,010
思维殿堂 好像全世界都在他的脑中
The Mind Palace, it's like a whole world in his head.

1217
01:04:00,010 --> 01:04:02,050
是啊 我需要回到那里
Yes, and I need to get back there.

1218
01:04:02,050 --> 01:04:05,930
思维殿堂是一种记忆技巧 我知道它能做什么事情
The Mind Palace is a memory technique, I know what it can do

1219
01:04:05,930 --> 01:04:08,800
我也知道它绝不能做什么事情
and I know what it most certainly cannot.

1220
01:04:08,800 --> 01:04:12,780
也许有一两件事 是我知道 而你却不知道的
Maybe there are one or two things that I know that you don't.

1221
01:04:13,510 --> 01:04:16,990
确实有 你列清单了吗
Oh, there are. Did you make a list?

1222
01:04:20,630 --> 01:04:21,490
你胖了
You've put on weight.

1223
01:04:21,490 --> 01:04:23,450
你穿的西装背心 明显要比夹克新
That waistcoat is clearly newer than the jacket.

1224
01:04:23,480 --> 01:04:25,750
够了 你列清单了吗
Stop this! Just stop it! Did you make a list?!

1225
01:04:25,770 --> 01:04:26,110
什么清单
Of what?

1226
01:04:26,170 --> 01:04:28,400
夏洛克 你摄入的所有东西
Everything, Sherlock. Everything you've taken.

1227
01:04:28,400 --> 01:04:29,450
不 他没有嗑药 嗑药后
No, it's not that, he goes

1228
01:04:29,460 --> 01:04:31,200
他会进入一种恍惚状态 我见过他那样
into a sort of trance. I've seen him do it.

1229
01:04:41,630 --> 01:04:46,500
从那一天起 我和我弟弟 就做了一个约定
We have an agreement, my brother and I, ever since that day.

1230
01:04:48,300 --> 01:04:49,520
不管我在哪里找到他
Wherever I find him,

1231
01:04:50,700 --> 01:04:53,130
无论是小胡同 还是廉价旅馆
whatever back alley or doss-house...

1232
01:04:54,550 --> 01:04:57,090
他都要给我列一个清单
there will always be a list.

1233
01:04:57,090 --> 01:04:59,370
他不可能在五分钟内 吸食这么多毒品
He couldn't have taken all that in the last five minutes.

1234
01:05:00,460 --> 01:05:02,680
他上飞机前 就已经嗑高了
He was high before he got on the plane.

1235
01:05:02,680 --> 01:05:04,040
他当时看上去可不像
He didn't seem high.

1236
01:05:04,050 --> 01:05:06,540
瘾君子最擅长伪装骗人了
Nobody deceives like an addict.

1237
01:05:06,540 --> 01:05:08,960
我不是瘾君子 我只是在利用毒品
I'm not an addict, I'm a user.

1238
01:05:08,960 --> 01:05:10,330
我这样来排解无聊
I alleviate boredom and

1239
01:05:10,330 --> 01:05:12,880
偶尔也用来加快思维进程
occasionally heighten my thought processes.

1240
01:05:12,880 --> 01:05:14,540
老天爷啊 这可是致命的
For God's sake! This could kill you!

1241
01:05:14,540 --> 01:05:17,540
- 你会死的 - 适量使用不会致命
- You could die! - Controlled usage is not usually fatal

1242
01:05:17,540 --> 01:05:20,000
何况禁欲也不会永生
and abstinence is not immortality.

1243
01:05:20,000 --> 01:05:21,130
你在干什么
What are you doing?

1244
01:05:21,130 --> 01:05:23,920
我在查艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂
Emelia Ricoletti, I'm looking her up.

1245
01:05:23,920 --> 01:05:25,370
我们是该查一查
Oh, I suppose we should.

1246
01:05:25,380 --> 01:05:28,290
我有军情五处资料的最高访问权
I have access to the top level of the MI5 archive.

1247
01:05:28,290 --> 01:05:30,170
我已经进去查了
Yep, that's where I'm looking.

1248
01:05:31,540 --> 01:05:33,540
你觉得军情五处的保卫系统怎么样
What do you think of MI5 security?

1249
01:05:34,870 --> 01:05:37,120
我觉得设立保卫系统 这个点子不错
I think it would be a good idea.

1250
01:05:38,290 --> 01:05:41,850
艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂 "悬案" 像他说的一样
Emelia Ricoletti, "Unsolved", like he says.

1251
01:05:41,880 --> 01:05:44,790
你们能不能安静一会儿 我得回去
Could you all just shut up for five minutes! I have to go back.

1252
01:05:44,790 --> 01:05:45,990
要不是你们跑上来乱叫
I was nearly there before

1253
01:05:45,990 --> 01:05:47,910
我马上就能解出来了
you stepped on and started yapping away!

1254
01:05:47,910 --> 01:05:50,330
"乱叫" 不好意思 是我们打断了你的思路吗
"Yapping?" Sorry, did we interrupt your session?

1255
01:05:50,330 --> 01:05:53,080
- 夏洛克 听我说 - 不听 你只会说个没完没了
- Sherlock, listen to me. - No, it only encourages you.

1256
01:05:53,080 --> 01:05:55,120
- 我没生你的气 - 那我真松了口气啊
- I'm not angry with you. - Oh, that's a relief!

1257
01:05:55,120 --> 01:05:58,660
我本来一直担心 不 等等 我其实并不担心
I was really worried... No, hold on, I really wasn't.

1258
01:06:00,000 --> 01:06:01,750
我曾经救过你
I was there for you before.

1259
01:06:02,580 --> 01:06:04,250
下一次我也会救你
I'll be there for you again.

1260
01:06:06,290 --> 01:06:08,000
我会一直守护着你
I'll always be there for you.

1261
01:06:10,290 --> 01:06:11,410
这都是我的错
This was my fault.

1262
01:06:12,620 --> 01:06:15,160
这事跟你没关系
It was nothing to do with you.

1263
01:06:15,160 --> 01:06:17,390
我应该想到 在监狱里的那一周
A week in a prison cell, I should have realised.

1264
01:06:17,420 --> 01:06:19,410
- 想到什么 - 对你来说
- Realised what? - That, in your case,

1265
01:06:19,410 --> 01:06:21,150
单独监禁是把你
solitary confinement is

1266
01:06:21,150 --> 01:06:23,160
和最强大的敌人 锁在了一起
locking you up with your worst enemy.

1267
01:06:23,160 --> 01:06:25,660
- 老天爷啊 - 吗啡还是可卡因
- Oh, for God's sake! - Morphine or cocaine?

1268
01:06:28,490 --> 01:06:31,620
- 你说什么 - 我什么都没说
- What did you say? - I didn't say anything.

1269
01:06:31,620 --> 01:06:33,530
不 你说了 你说
No, you did, you said...

1270
01:06:33,860 --> 01:06:36,610
今天又是哪种毒品 吗啡还是可卡因
Which is it today? Morphine or cocaine.

1271
01:06:39,160 --> 01:06:40,370
福尔摩斯
Holmes?

1272
01:06:40,370 --> 01:06:42,910
吗啡还是可卡因 你今天用的哪种毒品
Morphine or cocaine... which is it today?

1273
01:06:42,910 --> 01:06:45,220
回答我 该死的
Answer me, damn it!

1274
01:06:46,780 --> 01:06:48,420
莫里亚蒂来过了
Moriarty was here.

1275
01:06:49,370 --> 01:06:50,570
莫里亚蒂已经死了
Moriarty's dead.

1276
01:06:53,450 --> 01:06:56,700
- 我刚在飞机上 - 你说什么
- I was on a jet. - A what?

1277
01:06:56,700 --> 01:06:58,360
你和迈克罗夫特都在那里
You were there, and Mycroft.

1278
01:06:59,450 --> 01:07:02,650
你没离开过这个房间 福尔摩斯
You haven't left these rooms, Holmes.

1279
01:07:02,660 --> 01:07:05,820
你甚至动也没动过
You... haven't... moved.

1280
01:07:05,820 --> 01:07:07,990
好吧 告诉我 吗啡还是可卡因
Now, tell me, morphine or cocaine?

1281
01:07:09,860 --> 01:07:12,860
可卡因 浓度百分之七的溶液
Cocaine. A 7% solution.

1282
01:07:14,360 --> 01:07:16,030
- 你要来点吗 - 不要
- Would you care to try it? - No.

1283
01:07:16,030 --> 01:07:17,700
但是我倒是愿意把你
But I would quite like to find

1284
01:07:17,700 --> 01:07:18,490
所有的可卡因都找出来
every ounce of the stuff

1285
01:07:18,490 --> 01:07:20,860
然后倒出窗外去
in your possession and pour it out of the window.

1286
01:07:20,860 --> 01:07:22,530
那我得阻止你
I should be inclined to stop you.

1287
01:07:22,530 --> 01:07:25,360
那你会被强迫面对现实
Then you would be reminded, quite forcibly,

1288
01:07:25,360 --> 01:07:28,900
看清咱们俩谁是军人 谁又是瘾君子
which of us is a soldier and which of us a drug addict.

1289
01:07:28,900 --> 01:07:30,940
你不是军人 你是个医生
You're not a soldier, you are a doctor.

1290
01:07:30,940 --> 01:07:32,190
我是军医
I'm an army doctor,

1291
01:07:32,190 --> 01:07:33,330
也就是说我能边打碎
which means I could break

1292
01:07:33,330 --> 01:07:35,230
你身上的每一根骨头 一边说出它们的学名
every bone in your body while naming them.

1293
01:07:35,240 --> 01:07:39,400
亲爱的华生 你让情感蒙蔽了判断力
My dear Watson, you are allowing emotion to cloud your judgment.

1294
01:07:39,400 --> 01:07:41,400
绝不这么做
Never on a case.

1295
01:07:41,400 --> 01:07:43,150
你答应过我 绝不这么做的
You promised me, never on a case.

1296
01:07:43,390 --> 01:07:46,050
不 这只不过是 你故事中写的而已
No, I just said that in one of your stories.

1297
01:07:46,070 --> 01:07:49,890
听着 我乐意为了你装傻
Listen, I'm happy to play the fool for you.

1298
01:07:49,890 --> 01:07:52,720
如果你想 我会像个白痴一样 跟在你身后
I will run along behind you like some halfwit,

1299
01:07:52,720 --> 01:07:54,970
让你看上去更机智一些
making you look clever, if that's what you need.

1300
01:07:54,970 --> 01:07:59,890
但是老天爷啊 你得对自己 要求更高一些
But dear God above, you will hold yourself to a higher standard!

1301
01:07:59,890 --> 01:08:01,970
- 为什么 - 因为人们需要你这样做
- Why? - Because people need you to.

1302
01:08:01,970 --> 01:08:04,260
什么人 为什么 就因为你那些愚蠢的故事吗
What people, why? Because of your idiot stories?

1303
01:08:04,260 --> 01:08:06,550
是啊 就因为我那些愚蠢的故事
Yes, because of my "Idiot stories".

1304
01:08:06,550 --> 01:08:08,430
福尔摩斯先生
Mr. Holmes!

1305
01:08:09,410 --> 01:08:11,370
福尔摩斯先生 有电报 福尔摩斯先生
Mr. Holmes, telegram, Mr. Holmes.

1306
01:08:20,430 --> 01:08:22,720
是什么 出什么事了
What is it? What's wrong?

1307
01:08:22,720 --> 01:08:25,050
- 是玛丽 - 玛丽 她怎么了
- It's Mary. - Mary? What about her?

1308
01:08:25,050 --> 01:08:27,550
- 她很有可能有危险 - 什么危险
- It's entirely possible she's in danger. - Danger?

1309
01:08:27,550 --> 01:08:31,720
- 没时间解释了 - 你是嗑高了 在说胡话吗
- There's not a moment to lose. - Is this the cocaine talking?

1310
01:08:31,720 --> 01:08:33,130
玛丽能有什么危险
What danger could Mary be in?

1311
01:08:33,130 --> 01:08:35,450
我确定她正和朋友在一起呢
I'm sure she's just visiting with friends.

1312
01:08:35,470 --> 01:08:36,470
快来
Come on!

1313
01:08:42,090 --> 01:08:46,010
发生了什么事 你神智还清醒吗
What is happening? Are you even in a fit state?

1314
01:08:46,010 --> 01:08:49,380
为了玛丽的事 当然了 别在这一点上怀疑我 华生
For Mary, of course. Never doubt that, Watson.

1315
01:08:49,380 --> 01:08:51,260
别再这么做了
Never that.

1316
01:08:51,260 --> 01:08:52,960
福尔摩斯
Holmes?

1317
01:08:52,970 --> 01:08:54,300
我没事 我没事
I'm fine. I'm fine!

1318
01:08:56,220 --> 01:08:57,550
别戴那顶帽子
Not that one!

1319
01:08:58,720 --> 01:09:00,670
戴这顶帽子
This one.

1320
01:09:00,670 --> 01:09:03,380
- 为什么 - 你是夏洛克·福尔摩斯 戴你该戴的帽子
- Why? - You're Sherlock Holmes. Wear the damn hat.

1321
01:09:10,920 --> 01:09:12,590
马车 马车
Cab! Cab!

1322
01:09:16,340 --> 01:09:18,500
告诉我 她在哪里
So tell me, where is she?

1323
01:09:18,500 --> 01:09:20,540
你必须告诉我 发生了什么事情
You must tell me, what's going on?!

1324
01:09:20,550 --> 01:09:21,880
老好人华生
Oh, good old Watson!

1325
01:09:21,880 --> 01:09:24,460
你不问点问题 咱们还真没事干啊
How would we fill the time if you didn't ask questions?!

1326
01:09:24,460 --> 01:09:28,130
夏洛克 快说我老婆在哪里 混蛋
Sherlock, tell me where my bloody wife is, you pompous prick,

1327
01:09:28,130 --> 01:09:29,920
不然我就揍得你两眼发黑
or I'll punch your lights out!

1328
01:09:31,590 --> 01:09:32,880
福尔摩斯 她在哪里
Holmes, where is she?

1329
01:09:34,710 --> 01:09:35,960
她在一座废弃的教堂里
A de-sanctified church.

1330
01:09:35,960 --> 01:09:37,810
她觉得自己发现了解决办法
She thinks she's found the solution and,

1331
01:09:37,820 --> 01:09:39,250
就因为这个原因
for no better reason than that,

1332
01:09:39,250 --> 01:09:42,080
她将自己置身于 巨大的危机中
she's put herself in the path of considerable danger.

1333
01:09:42,090 --> 01:09:44,080
你真是选了个好老婆啊
What an excellent choice of wife.

1334
01:09:56,960 --> 01:09:58,210
真是见鬼了
What the devil?!

1335
01:09:58,210 --> 01:09:59,580
我找到她们了
I've found them.

1336
01:10:08,080 --> 01:10:11,410
- 这是什么情况 玛丽 - 这是整件事的核心 约翰
- What is all this, Mary? - This is the heart of it all, John.

1337
01:10:11,410 --> 01:10:13,330
这是整个阴谋的关键
The heart of the conspiracy.

1338
01:10:33,580 --> 01:10:36,580
天啊 这是什么地方
Great God, what is this place?

1339
01:10:36,580 --> 01:10:38,740
你到底在这里做什么
And what the devil are you doing here?!

1340
01:10:38,750 --> 01:10:41,160
我一直在做调查
I've been making enquiries.

1341
01:10:41,160 --> 01:10:42,910
福尔摩斯先生让我做的
Mr. Holmes asked me.

1342
01:10:42,910 --> 01:10:44,240
福尔摩斯 你怎么能这样做
Holmes, how could you?

1343
01:10:44,240 --> 01:10:45,910
不是他 是更聪明那个福尔摩斯
No, not him, the clever one.

1344
01:10:46,990 --> 01:10:48,230
我觉得很明显
It seemed obvious to me

1345
01:10:48,230 --> 01:10:50,700
这件事情不可能是独自策划的
that this business could not be managed alone.

1346
01:10:50,700 --> 01:10:53,410
我认为瑞克莱蒂太太有帮手
My theory is that Mrs. Ricoletti had help.

1347
01:10:53,410 --> 01:10:54,990
她的朋友在帮她
Help from her friends.

1348
01:10:54,990 --> 01:10:57,160
真精彩 玛丽 "更聪明的那位福尔摩斯"
Bravo, Mary. "The clever one?"

1349
01:10:58,280 --> 01:10:59,870
我 我以为要失去你了
I... I thought I was losing you.

1350
01:11:01,370 --> 01:11:03,450
我以为我们一直在
I thought perhaps we were...

1351
01:11:03,450 --> 01:11:06,070
- 忽视彼此 - 是你要搬出去的
- neglecting each other. - Well, you're the one who moved out.

1352
01:11:06,080 --> 01:11:07,530
我在跟玛丽说话
I was talking to Mary.

1353
01:11:09,200 --> 01:11:10,740
你在替迈克罗夫特工作吗
You're working for Mycroft?

1354
01:11:10,740 --> 01:11:12,950
他想监视这位疯狂的兄弟
He likes to keep an eye on his mad sibling.

1355
01:11:12,950 --> 01:11:15,410
手边还有个间谍做任务 你没发现
And he had a spy to hand. Has it never occurred to you

1356
01:11:15,410 --> 01:11:17,550
你妻子作为一个护士 有点太能干了吗
your wife is excessively skilled for a nurse?

1357
01:11:17,600 --> 01:11:21,240
当然没发现 因为他知道护士的能力所在
Of course it hasn't, because he knows what a nurse is capable of.

1358
01:11:21,240 --> 01:11:23,610
- 你什么时候开始这么想的 - 就刚刚
- When did it occur to you? - Only now, I'm afraid.

1359
01:11:23,610 --> 01:11:27,280
作为一个反应慢的小弟弟 你一定过得很辛苦吧
Must be difficult, being the slow little brother.

1360
01:11:27,280 --> 01:11:29,950
真是不堪回首 我们说得够多了 还是集中注意力吧
Time I sped up. Enough chatter, let's concentrate.

1361
01:11:29,950 --> 01:11:32,240
你说得对 这是怎么回事
Yes, all right. What's all this about?

1362
01:11:33,280 --> 01:11:34,740
他们要干什么
What do they want to accomplish?

1363
01:11:34,740 --> 01:11:36,070
我们为何不走近弄个明白
Why don't we go and find out.

1364
01:11:55,570 --> 01:11:57,610
抱歉 我见锣就想敲
Sorry! I can never resist a gong.

1365
01:11:57,610 --> 01:12:00,610
- 见到闹剧 就想插一脚 - 真是没想到
- Or a touch of the dramatic. - Never have guessed!

1366
01:12:00,610 --> 01:12:03,900
虽然在这方面 你们好像跟我一样热情
Though it seems you share my enthusiasm in that regard.

1367
01:12:05,400 --> 01:12:07,280
棒极了
Excellent.

1368
01:12:07,280 --> 01:12:08,690
顶级的剧场
Superlative theatre.

1369
01:12:09,860 --> 01:12:11,860
我真是欣赏这场面
I applaud the spectacle.

1370
01:12:15,150 --> 01:12:16,820
艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂饮弹自尽
Emelia Ricoletti shot herself,

1371
01:12:16,820 --> 01:12:20,360
然后死而复生 谋杀了她的丈夫
then apparently returned from the grave and killed her husband.

1372
01:12:20,360 --> 01:12:22,570
所以
So...

1373
01:12:22,570 --> 01:12:23,900
她是怎么做到的
how was it done?

1374
01:12:25,020 --> 01:12:26,900
我们来按顺序理清一下真相吧
Let's take the events in order.

1375
01:12:29,860 --> 01:12:30,740
瑞克莱蒂夫人用
Mrs. Ricoletti gets

1376
01:12:30,740 --> 01:12:32,940
非常有效的方式 吸引了所有人的注意
everyone's attention in very efficient fashion.

1377
01:12:32,940 --> 01:12:34,610
是你
You!

1378
01:12:36,730 --> 01:12:38,600
是你吗
You?!

1379
01:12:38,610 --> 01:12:40,440
还是我
Or me?

1380
01:12:40,440 --> 01:12:42,520
她把一只手枪放进嘴里
She places one of the revolvers in her mouth,

1381
01:12:42,520 --> 01:12:44,850
实际上开火的 是另一只口朝下的枪
while actually firing the other into the ground.

1382
01:12:44,860 --> 01:12:46,940
她的同伙在窗帘上撒上了血液
An accomplice sprays the curtains with blood

1383
01:12:46,940 --> 01:12:48,400
因此楼下受惊的人们
and thus her apparent suicide

1384
01:12:48,400 --> 01:12:51,060
就都目击到了她的自杀
is witnessed by the frightened crowd below.

1385
01:12:52,400 --> 01:12:53,370
一具跟瑞克莱蒂太太十分相似的
A substitute corpse,

1386
01:12:53,370 --> 01:12:55,600
尸体取而代之出现在了她的位置
bearing a strong resemblance to Mrs. Ricoletti

1387
01:12:55,600 --> 01:12:58,390
并随后被送去了太平间
takes her place and is later transported to the morgue,

1388
01:12:58,400 --> 01:12:59,600
这对于苏格兰警察来说
a grubby little suicide

1389
01:12:59,600 --> 01:13:01,770
只是毫无兴趣的小自杀案
of little interest to Scotland Yard.

1390
01:13:01,770 --> 01:13:05,690
同时 真正的瑞克莱蒂夫人溜走了
Meanwhile, the real Mrs. Ricoletti slips away.

1391
01:13:10,390 --> 01:13:12,350
然后就到了十分聪明的环节了
Now comes the really clever part.

1392
01:13:12,350 --> 01:13:14,470
瑞克莱蒂夫人说服了
Mrs. Ricoletti persuaded a cab driver,

1393
01:13:14,470 --> 01:13:15,310
一位认识她的马车夫
someone who knew her,

1394
01:13:15,310 --> 01:13:18,980
在她丈夫最喜欢去的鸦片馆外截住了他
to intercept her husband outside his favourite opium den.

1395
01:13:18,980 --> 01:13:21,480
那里是上演一场绝妙闹剧的最佳舞台
The perfect stage for a perfect drama.

1396
01:13:22,560 --> 01:13:24,270
你是谁 你想做什么
Who are you? What do you want?

1397
01:13:26,520 --> 01:13:28,020
艾美莉亚
Emelia?

1398
01:13:28,020 --> 01:13:29,310
救命
Help!

1399
01:13:29,310 --> 01:13:31,600
完美的身份认证
A perfect positive identification.

1400
01:13:31,600 --> 01:13:33,930
瑞克莱蒂夫人死而复生
The late Mrs. Ricoletti has returned from the grave

1401
01:13:33,930 --> 01:13:35,930
加上高超的装扮
and a little skilled make-up

1402
01:13:35,930 --> 01:13:38,720
就塑造出了复仇怨灵的熊熊怒火
and you have nothing less than the wrath of a vengeful ghost.

1403
01:13:52,470 --> 01:13:54,930
最后只剩下一件事
There was only one thing left to do.

1404
01:13:54,930 --> 01:13:57,800
快点动手 你不必感到难过
Swiftly now. No tears.

1405
01:14:01,640 --> 01:14:04,590
最后只需将真的瑞克莱蒂夫人
All that remained was to substitute the real Mrs. Ricoletti

1406
01:14:04,600 --> 01:14:06,260
替换掉太平间里的假尸体就行了
for the corpse in the morgue.

1407
01:14:06,260 --> 01:14:09,220
这下 就算有人想要验尸
This time, should anyone attempt to identify her,

1408
01:14:09,220 --> 01:14:11,760
那也毫无疑问的就是她了
it would be positively, absolutely her.

1409
01:14:11,760 --> 01:14:13,800
但她为什么要这么做
But why would she do that?

1410
01:14:13,800 --> 01:14:15,510
为了证明观点而去死吗
Die to prove a point?

1411
01:14:15,510 --> 01:14:17,930
所有的伟业都有殉道者
Every great cause has martyrs.

1412
01:14:17,930 --> 01:14:22,590
所有战争都需要牺牲 没错 这就是一场战争
Every war has suicide missions and make no mistake, this is war.

1413
01:14:22,590 --> 01:14:25,380
半数的人类正在与另外半数交战
One half of the human race at war with the other.

1414
01:14:26,680 --> 01:14:30,470
一支近在咫尺的无形军队
The invisible army hovering at our elbow,

1415
01:14:30,470 --> 01:14:32,590
照料着我们的家园
tending to our homes,

1416
01:14:32,590 --> 01:14:33,970
养育着我们的孩子
raising our children.

1417
01:14:35,550 --> 01:14:37,880
他们却被忽视着 被轻视着
Ignored, patronised,

1418
01:14:37,880 --> 01:14:39,550
被蔑视着
disregarded.

1419
01:14:40,920 --> 01:14:43,340
甚至不允许有投票的权利
Not allowed so much as a vote.

1420
01:14:52,670 --> 01:14:54,550
然而这毕竟是支军队
But an army nonetheless,

1421
01:14:54,550 --> 01:14:57,670
她们已经为了崇高的伟业而崛起
ready to rise up in the best of causes.

1422
01:14:57,670 --> 01:15:01,880
纠正人类有史以来就固存的不公
To put right an injustice as old as humanity itself.

1423
01:15:04,550 --> 01:15:07,300
华生 你看 迈克罗夫特说得对
So you see, Watson, Mycroft was right.

1424
01:15:07,300 --> 01:15:09,170
这是一场我们必定会输的战争
This is a war we must lose.

1425
01:15:09,170 --> 01:15:10,590
她已经病入膏肓了
She was dying.

1426
01:15:11,880 --> 01:15:14,170
- 谁 - 艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂
- Who was? - Emelia Ricoletti.

1427
01:15:14,170 --> 01:15:16,940
她有明显的肺病症状
There were clear signs of consumption...

1428
01:15:16,960 --> 01:15:18,880
她应该不久于世了
I doubt she wasn't long for this world.

1429
01:15:18,880 --> 01:15:21,170
所以她决定让自己死得其所
So she decided to make her death count.

1430
01:15:23,500 --> 01:15:26,580
她对美国的秘密社交圈很熟悉
She was already familiar with the secret societies of America.

1431
01:15:26,590 --> 01:15:28,500
并且她有办法
And was able to draw on their methods of fear

1432
01:15:28,500 --> 01:15:30,960
公开敞亮地进行威胁恐吓
and intimidation to publicly, very publicly,

1433
01:15:30,960 --> 01:15:34,420
逼尤斯塔斯·卡迈克尔爵士 直面他犯下的罪恶
confront Sir Eustace Carmichael with the sins of his past.

1434
01:15:34,420 --> 01:15:36,130
他在美国就认识她了
He knew her out in the States.

1435
01:15:38,580 --> 01:15:40,420
许诺给她一切
Promised her everything.

1436
01:15:40,420 --> 01:15:42,710
婚姻 地位
Marriage, position.

1437
01:15:44,710 --> 01:15:47,290
之后他不过是玩弄她
And then he had his way with her...

1438
01:15:48,380 --> 01:15:50,330
抛弃她
and threw her over.

1439
01:15:50,330 --> 01:15:53,330
留她一人 身无分文
Left her abandoned and penniless.

1440
01:15:53,330 --> 01:15:54,620
霍珀
Hooper!

1441
01:16:00,040 --> 01:16:02,460
福尔摩斯
Holmes.

1442
01:16:02,460 --> 01:16:06,080
郑重声明 福尔摩斯 她可没骗过我
For the record, Holmes, she didn't have me fooled.

1443
01:16:10,540 --> 01:16:12,500
为什么你从不提及我 先生
Why do you never mention me, sir?

1444
01:16:16,160 --> 01:16:20,410
艾美莉亚以为 和瑞克莱蒂在一起就能幸福
Emelia thought that she'd found happiness with Ricoletti,

1445
01:16:20,880 --> 01:16:23,180
但他也是个畜生
but he was a brute too.

1446
01:16:28,770 --> 01:16:31,680
艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂是我们的朋友
Emelia Ricoletti was our friend.

1447
01:16:31,680 --> 01:16:34,390
你根本想不到 那个混账如何对待她
You have no idea how that bastard treated her.

1448
01:16:36,270 --> 01:16:39,890
但新娘呢 福尔摩斯 我们看到过她的
But the Bride, Holmes, we saw her.

1449
01:16:39,890 --> 01:16:41,100
没错 华生 我们看到过
Yes, Watson, we did.

1450
01:16:42,140 --> 01:16:44,140
那个碎玻璃的声音吗
The sound of breaking glass?

1451
01:16:44,140 --> 01:16:46,100
当时碎的不是窗户
Not a window,

1452
01:16:46,100 --> 01:16:48,390
这不过是古老的戏剧诡计
just an old theatrical trick.

1453
01:16:48,390 --> 01:16:51,760
- 这不可能是真的 福尔摩斯 - 是不可能
- It cannot be true, Holmes, it cannot! - No, it can't.

1454
01:16:51,770 --> 01:16:54,430
那叫做佩珀尔幻象
It's called Pepper's Ghost.

1455
01:16:55,560 --> 01:16:59,850
在镜中反射出活人的身影
A simple reflection in glass of a living, breathing person.

1456
01:17:01,220 --> 01:17:05,010
他们唯一的纰漏 就是弄碎了玻璃
Their only mistake was breaking the glass when they removed it.'

1457
01:17:07,640 --> 01:17:08,720
看看四周
Look around you.

1458
01:17:09,930 --> 01:17:11,970
房间里全是新娘
This room is full of brides.

1459
01:17:18,300 --> 01:17:20,220
一旦她站出来
Once she had risen,

1460
01:17:20,220 --> 01:17:21,720
任何人都能成为她
anyone could be her.

1461
01:17:23,760 --> 01:17:26,090
复仇的鬼魂
The avenging ghost.

1462
01:17:26,090 --> 01:17:28,970
是一个让心怀恶意的男人
A legend to strike terror into the heart of any man

1463
01:17:28,970 --> 01:17:30,970
恐惧不已的传说
with malicious intent.

1464
01:17:30,970 --> 01:17:33,720
一个追踪没有得到恶报的混蛋
A spectre to stalk those unpunished brutes

1465
01:17:33,720 --> 01:17:35,840
要与之清算过去的幽灵
whose reckoning is long overdue.

1466
01:17:36,930 --> 01:17:40,090
复仇女神觉醒了
A league of furies awakened.

1467
01:17:40,090 --> 01:17:41,840
那位我
The women I...

1468
01:17:41,840 --> 01:17:44,590
我们 欺骗过背叛过的女人
WE have lied to, betrayed.

1469
01:17:46,590 --> 01:17:49,590
我们忽视和蔑视的女人
The women we have ignored and disparaged.

1470
01:17:57,760 --> 01:18:00,130
一旦产生了这样的想法
Once the idea exists,

1471
01:18:00,130 --> 01:18:01,420
就难很消除了
it cannot be killed.

1472
01:18:03,050 --> 01:18:05,960
一个目标坚定的人才能做到这样
This is the work of a single-minded person.

1473
01:18:05,970 --> 01:18:10,590
她还非常了解 尤斯塔斯爵士的精神虐待
Someone who knew first-hand about Sir Eustace's mental cruelty.

1474
01:18:10,590 --> 01:18:12,960
了解他阴暗的秘密
The dark secret,

1475
01:18:12,960 --> 01:18:15,210
这只有她最好的朋友才知道
kept from all but her closest friends,

1476
01:18:15,210 --> 01:18:17,010
包括艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂
including Emelia Ricoletti...

1477
01:18:18,210 --> 01:18:21,630
这位曾多年前遭受丈夫虐待的女人
the woman her husband wronged all those years before.

1478
01:18:23,170 --> 01:18:25,920
如果忽略鬼魂
If one disregards the ghost,

1479
01:18:25,920 --> 01:18:27,550
那就只有一个嫌疑人了
there is only one suspect.

1480
01:18:29,000 --> 01:18:31,340
是吧 卡迈克尔夫人
Isn't that right, Lady Carmichael?

1481
01:18:34,050 --> 01:18:37,460
但还有个小地方 我不太明白
One small detail doesn't quite make sense to me, however.

1482
01:18:39,630 --> 01:18:42,040
为什么要找我来阻止
Why engage me to prevent

1483
01:18:42,040 --> 01:18:45,080
这件你打算实施的谋杀
a murder you intended to commit?

1484
01:18:47,500 --> 01:18:50,460
"我不太明白 不应该是这样啊"
"Doesn't quite make sense, doesn't quite make sense."

1485
01:18:50,460 --> 01:18:53,000
你当然不明白 因为这不是真的
Of course it doesn't make sense, it's not real.

1486
01:18:54,210 --> 01:18:55,630
夏洛克
Oh, Sherlock.

1487
01:18:57,880 --> 01:19:00,540
躲猫猫
Peek-a-boo.

1488
01:19:00,540 --> 01:19:01,920
不
No.

1489
01:19:02,960 --> 01:19:04,750
不 不是你
No, not you.

1490
01:19:06,000 --> 01:19:07,290
不可能是你
It can't be you.

1491
01:19:07,290 --> 01:19:09,910
得了吧 好好想想
I mean, come on, be serious.

1492
01:19:09,920 --> 01:19:12,540
服装 锣
The costumes, the gong?

1493
01:19:12,540 --> 01:19:14,500
作为一个超级反派
Speaking as a criminal mastermind,

1494
01:19:14,500 --> 01:19:17,710
我们并没有真的锣 或者特殊的服装
we don't really have gongs or special outfits.

1495
01:19:19,410 --> 01:19:20,910
这到底是怎么回事
What the hell is going on?

1496
01:19:22,660 --> 01:19:24,460
这对你来说够蠢吗
Is this silly enough for you yet?

1497
01:19:25,910 --> 01:19:29,250
哥特风够浓吗 够疯狂吗 即使对你而言
Gothic enough? Mad enough, even for you?

1498
01:19:29,250 --> 01:19:33,390
你想不明白 夏洛克 是因为这不是真的
It doesn't make sense, Sherlock, because it's not real.

1499
01:19:33,910 --> 01:19:36,950
- 一切都不是真的 - 他在说什么
- None of it. - What's he talking about?

1500
01:19:36,950 --> 01:19:38,580
这些都是你的幻想
This is all in your mind.

1501
01:19:40,330 --> 01:19:41,510
夏洛克
Sherlock?

1502
01:19:42,580 --> 01:19:43,640
福尔摩斯
Holmes!

1503
01:19:44,160 --> 01:19:45,830
你在做梦
You're dreaming.

1504
01:19:45,830 --> 01:19:47,490
他在做梦吗
Is he dreaming?

1505
01:19:49,910 --> 01:19:51,580
他醒了
And there he is.

1506
01:19:51,580 --> 01:19:53,280
我们还以为 你要死了呢
Thought we'd lost you for a moment.

1507
01:19:53,290 --> 01:19:56,490
容我问一下 这就是你说的"控制用量"吗
May I just check, is this what you mean by "Controlled usage"?

1508
01:19:56,490 --> 01:19:59,660
艾美莉亚·瑞克莱蒂太太 告诉我她埋在哪里
Mrs. Emelia Ricoletti, I need to know where she was buried.

1509
01:19:59,660 --> 01:20:03,330
- 一百二十年前被埋在哪里吗 - 是的
- What, 120 years ago? - Yes.

1510
01:20:03,330 --> 01:20:06,410
如果还有记录 也得花几周时间来查
That would take weeks to find, if those records even exists.

1511
01:20:06,410 --> 01:20:08,620
- 即使是动用我的资源 - 查到了
- Even with my resources. - Got it.

1512
01:20:11,160 --> 01:20:13,120
我不明白 这一切有什么关联
I don't get it, how is this relevant?

1513
01:20:13,120 --> 01:20:15,030
我要知道自己是对的 然后我才能肯定
I need to know I was right, then I'll be sure.

1514
01:20:15,030 --> 01:20:16,530
- 你是说莫里亚蒂怎么做到的 - 没错
- You mean how Moriarty did it? - Yes.

1515
01:20:16,530 --> 01:20:18,950
但这些都不是真实发生的 是你自己想的
But none of that really happened, it was in your head.

1516
01:20:18,950 --> 01:20:20,530
我的调查是幻想中的
My investigation was the fantasy,

1517
01:20:20,530 --> 01:20:22,450
但犯罪方式和我的解释一样
the crime happened exactly as I explained.

1518
01:20:22,450 --> 01:20:24,570
墓碑是她朋友们立的
The stone was erected by a group of her friends.

1519
01:20:24,570 --> 01:20:26,270
你想在这里找什么
I don't know what you think you'll find here.

1520
01:20:26,290 --> 01:20:27,830
我得试试
I need to try!

1521
01:20:35,660 --> 01:20:37,060
瑞克莱蒂太太被埋在这里
Mrs. Ricoletti was buried here,

1522
01:20:37,060 --> 01:20:38,650
但另一具尸体呢
but what happened to the other one?

1523
01:20:38,660 --> 01:20:41,820
在那场所谓的自杀后 代替她的尸体
The corpse they substituted for her after the so-called suicide?

1524
01:20:41,820 --> 01:20:44,200
- 他们肯定搬走了 - 但搬到哪里去了
- They'd move it, of course they would. - But where?

1525
01:20:44,200 --> 01:20:45,860
反正不在这里
Well, not here.

1526
01:20:45,860 --> 01:20:48,280
但他们肯定会这么做
But that... That's exactly what they must have done.

1527
01:20:48,280 --> 01:20:50,280
同谋者都是有内应的
The conspirators had someone on the inside.

1528
01:20:50,280 --> 01:20:51,310
他们找到一具尸体
They found a body, just

1529
01:20:51,310 --> 01:20:53,360
就像莫莉·霍珀给我找了具尸体
like Molly Hooper found a body for me, when...

1530
01:20:53,360 --> 01:20:55,860
我们不用再说一遍那件事了 对吧
Yeah, well, we don't need to go into all that again, do we?

1531
01:20:55,860 --> 01:20:57,610
你不是真的要这样做吧
You're not seriously going to do this?

1532
01:20:57,610 --> 01:20:59,940
我们就是为这个来的 我需要答案
It's why we came here. I need to know.

1533
01:20:59,940 --> 01:21:01,440
简直是瘾君子的口吻
Spoken like an addict.

1534
01:21:01,440 --> 01:21:04,400
- 这对我来说很重要 - 不 这说明你得接受治疗
- This is important to me! - No, this is you needing a fix.

1535
01:21:04,400 --> 01:21:05,860
- 约翰 - 莫里亚蒂回来了
- John... - Moriarty's back.

1536
01:21:05,860 --> 01:21:08,590
我们有案子 真实生活中 我们有问题需要解决
We have a case, we have a real-life problem right now.

1537
01:21:08,620 --> 01:21:11,200
等一下就解决它 先让我把这事做完
Getting to that, it's next on the list. Just let me do this.

1538
01:21:11,200 --> 01:21:13,530
不行 大家总是让你为所欲为
No, everyone always lets you do whatever you want.

1539
01:21:13,530 --> 01:21:15,410
- 所以你才变成现在这样 - 约翰 拜托
- That's how you got in this state! - John, please...

1540
01:21:15,440 --> 01:21:17,760
这次我不奉陪了 夏洛克 再也不了
I'm not playing this time, Sherlock. Not any more!

1541
01:21:18,630 --> 01:21:20,710
等你准备好工作了 再给我打电话
When you're ready to go to work, give me a call.

1542
01:21:20,710 --> 01:21:22,580
- 我要带玛丽回家了 - 你说什么
- I'm taking Mary home. - You're what?

1543
01:21:22,580 --> 01:21:24,460
- 玛丽要带我回家了 - 这还差不多
- Mary's taking me home. - Better.

1544
01:21:26,710 --> 01:21:28,830
- 他说得对 - 那又怎样
- He's right, you know. - So what if he's right?!

1545
01:21:28,830 --> 01:21:30,330
他总是对的 这太无聊了
He's always right, it's boring!

1546
01:21:33,290 --> 01:21:34,710
你会帮我吗
Will you help me?

1547
01:21:38,870 --> 01:21:40,330
找出那个女人
Cherchez la femme.

1548
01:22:26,620 --> 01:22:28,280
上帝啊
Oh, dear.

1549
01:22:28,290 --> 01:22:29,580
这里已经囊空如洗了
The cupboard is bare.

1550
01:22:31,740 --> 01:22:33,990
他们肯定把她埋在下面了
They must have buried it underneath.

1551
01:22:33,990 --> 01:22:36,870
肯定埋在棺材下面了
They must have buried it underneath the coffin.

1552
01:22:51,240 --> 01:22:52,780
你运气不好啊 夏洛克
Bad luck, Sherlock.

1553
01:22:54,700 --> 01:22:56,950
或许他们用其他方式处理了尸体
Maybe they got rid of the body in another way.

1554
01:22:56,980 --> 01:22:58,440
- 不 - 很有可能
- No... - More than likely.

1555
01:22:58,780 --> 01:23:00,780
毕竟这是很久以前的事了
At any rate, it was a very long time ago.

1556
01:23:00,780 --> 01:23:02,070
我们眼下还有
We do have slightly more

1557
01:23:02,070 --> 01:23:04,280
更紧迫的事要办 弟弟
pressing matters to hand, little brother.

1558
01:23:04,280 --> 01:23:06,700
莫里亚蒂 死而复生
Moriarty? Back from the dead?

1559
01:23:06,700 --> 01:23:10,950
勿忘我
Do not forget me.

1560
01:23:10,950 --> 01:23:15,740
勿忘我
Do not forget me!

1561
01:23:29,780 --> 01:23:31,570
这里
This?

1562
01:23:31,570 --> 01:23:32,860
我明白了
Oh, I see.

1563
01:23:34,530 --> 01:23:36,400
我还是没醒 对吧
Still not awake, am I?

1564
01:24:03,860 --> 01:24:05,860
太深了 夏洛克 你陷得太深了
Too deep, Sherlock, way too deep.

1565
01:24:07,340 --> 01:24:09,860
恭喜你 将会成为有史以来第一位
Congratulations, you will be the first man in history

1566
01:24:09,980 --> 01:24:12,060
埋在自己思维殿堂里的人
to be buried in his own Mind Palace.

1567
01:24:14,310 --> 01:24:17,100
这场景也太夸张了 你不觉得吗
The setting is a shade melodramatic, don't you think?

1568
01:24:17,100 --> 01:24:18,480
对你我而言
For you and me?

1569
01:24:19,810 --> 01:24:21,180
一点都不夸张
Not at all.

1570
01:24:24,020 --> 01:24:26,100
你到底是什么东西
What are you?

1571
01:24:26,100 --> 01:24:28,180
你知道我是什么东西
You know what I am.

1572
01:24:28,180 --> 01:24:30,100
我是莫里亚蒂
I'm Moriarty.

1573
01:24:30,100 --> 01:24:31,890
犯罪界的拿破仑
The Napoleon of Crime.

1574
01:24:31,890 --> 01:24:34,430
- 莫里亚蒂已经死了 - 在你脑中可没有
- Moriarty's dead! - Not in your mind.

1575
01:24:34,430 --> 01:24:36,760
我在你的脑海里永存
I'll never be dead there.

1576
01:24:36,760 --> 01:24:39,760
你曾把自己的大脑称为硬盘
You once called your brain a hard drive.

1577
01:24:39,760 --> 01:24:41,470
现在 和病毒打声招呼吧
Well, say hello to the virus.

1578
01:24:42,760 --> 01:24:44,430
这就是我们的结局
This is how we end, you and I.

1579
01:24:45,640 --> 01:24:47,760
永远在这里
Always here,

1580
01:24:47,760 --> 01:24:49,140
永远都在一起
always together.

1581
01:24:51,550 --> 01:24:55,050
你的想法很棒 莫里亚蒂
You have a magnificent brain, Moriarty.

1582
01:24:55,050 --> 01:24:57,010
我很佩服
I admire it.

1583
01:24:57,010 --> 01:25:00,800
我承认或许 它能和我的大脑相提并论
I concede it may even be the equal of my own.

1584
01:25:00,800 --> 01:25:02,220
我很感动
I'm touched.

1585
01:25:04,590 --> 01:25:06,050
我很荣幸
I'm honoured.

1586
01:25:06,050 --> 01:25:08,760
但说到在悬崖边上
But when it comes to the matter of unarmed combat

1587
01:25:08,760 --> 01:25:10,870
徒手格斗
on the edge of a precipice...

1588
01:25:12,260 --> 01:25:14,760
你只有落水的份
you're going in the water,

1589
01:25:14,760 --> 01:25:17,130
小个子
short-arse.

1590
01:25:29,300 --> 01:25:32,090
你觉得自己很高大勇猛吗 夏洛克
Oh, you think you're so big and strong, Sherlock!

1591
01:25:32,370 --> 01:25:33,660
我可不敢苟同
Not with me.

1592
01:25:47,540 --> 01:25:49,580
我就是你的弱点
I am your weakness!

1593
01:25:51,540 --> 01:25:53,330
我能打倒你
I keep you down!

1594
01:25:54,700 --> 01:25:58,540
你的每一次跌倒 失败
Every time you stumble, every time you fail,

1595
01:25:58,540 --> 01:26:00,120
每一次的弱势
when you're weak,

1596
01:26:00,120 --> 01:26:02,370
我都
I... am...

1597
01:26:02,370 --> 01:26:03,910
在那里
there!

1598
01:26:06,370 --> 01:26:07,950
不
No,

1599
01:26:07,950 --> 01:26:09,740
你别再试着抵抗了
don't try to fight it.

1600
01:26:09,740 --> 01:26:11,370
躺好认输吧
Lie back and lose!

1601
01:26:17,620 --> 01:26:19,990
我们一起跳下去吧
Shall we go over together?

1602
01:26:19,990 --> 01:26:21,820
必须是一起跳 对吧
It has to be together, doesn't it?

1603
01:26:21,830 --> 01:26:25,240
最终 永远都是
At the end it's always just you

1604
01:26:25,240 --> 01:26:27,240
你和我
and me!

1605
01:26:32,820 --> 01:26:35,700
教授 麻烦你离我的朋友远一点
Professor, if you wouldn't mind stepping away from my friend,

1606
01:26:35,700 --> 01:26:39,110
我相信 他很讨厌你的行为
I do believe he finds your attention a shade annoying.

1607
01:26:41,610 --> 01:26:44,780
这不公平 你们有两个人
That's not fair, there's two of you!

1608
01:26:44,780 --> 01:26:47,160
我们一直是两个人 你没看过斯特兰德报吗
There's always two of us. Don't you read The Strand?

1609
01:26:49,280 --> 01:26:50,860
跪下 教授
On your knees, Professor.

1610
01:26:55,530 --> 01:26:57,950
把手放到头上
Hands behind your head.

1611
01:26:59,240 --> 01:27:00,570
谢谢你 约翰
Thank you, John.

1612
01:27:02,450 --> 01:27:04,240
你什么时候开始叫我约翰了
Since when do you call me John?

1613
01:27:05,280 --> 01:27:07,030
生活处处充满惊喜
You'd be surprised.

1614
01:27:07,030 --> 01:27:08,360
那倒未必
No, I wouldn't.

1615
01:27:10,860 --> 01:27:12,530
该醒来了 夏洛克
Time you woke up, Sherlock.

1616
01:27:14,440 --> 01:27:17,280
我是写故事的人 我知道自己在哪里
I'm a story-teller, I know when I'm in one.

1617
01:27:17,280 --> 01:27:19,190
当然
Of course.

1618
01:27:19,190 --> 01:27:20,570
你当然知道 约翰
Of course you do, John.

1619
01:27:21,650 --> 01:27:23,150
那他长什么样
So what's he like?

1620
01:27:23,150 --> 01:27:25,610
另一个世界的我
The other me in the other place?

1621
01:27:27,030 --> 01:27:29,020
比他看上去更聪明
Smarter than he looks.

1622
01:27:29,030 --> 01:27:30,530
那肯定是聪明绝顶了
Pretty damn smart, then.

1623
01:27:31,820 --> 01:27:33,360
是 聪明绝顶
Pretty damn smart.

1624
01:27:33,360 --> 01:27:37,270
天啊 你俩干脆直接私奔吧
Ugh, why don't you two just elope, for God's sake?!

1625
01:27:37,270 --> 01:27:39,110
你真是粗鲁
Impertinent.

1626
01:27:39,110 --> 01:27:40,900
你真是无礼
Offensive.

1627
01:27:40,900 --> 01:27:43,650
介意我来吗
Actually, would you mind?

1628
01:27:43,650 --> 01:27:44,860
一点也不
Not at all.

1629
01:27:54,770 --> 01:27:57,520
- 总算轮到我了 - 是啊
- It was my turn. - Quite so.

1630
01:27:57,520 --> 01:27:59,190
你打算怎么醒过来
So how do you plan to wake up?

1631
01:28:03,060 --> 01:28:04,560
我觉得应该这样做
I should think like this.

1632
01:28:06,440 --> 01:28:08,270
你确定吗
Are you sure?

1633
01:28:08,270 --> 01:28:11,600
只限于我们之间的秘密 约翰 坠落是杀不死我的
Between you and me, John, I always survive a fall.

1634
01:28:11,600 --> 01:28:12,900
可你怎么做到的
But how?

1635
01:28:14,440 --> 01:28:16,150
很简单 亲爱的华生
Elementary, my dear Watson.

1636
01:28:49,770 --> 01:28:51,470
- 想我了吗 - 夏洛克 你还好吗
- Miss me? - Sherlock, are you all right?

1637
01:28:51,470 --> 01:28:53,220
当然 我为什么不好
Yes. Of course I am, why wouldn't I be?

1638
01:28:53,220 --> 01:28:55,970
因为你可能服药过量 你应该去医院
Because you probably just OD'd. You should be in hospital.

1639
01:28:55,970 --> 01:28:57,760
没时间了
Hm, no time.

1640
01:28:57,770 --> 01:29:00,420
我现在得去贝克街 莫里亚蒂回来了
I have to go to Baker Street now, Moriarty's back.

1641
01:29:01,220 --> 01:29:02,810
我倒是希望他回来了
I almost hope he is,

1642
01:29:02,810 --> 01:29:05,110
如果这能让你不再沉浸于此
if it'll save you from this.

1643
01:29:07,720 --> 01:29:10,850
现在不需要这个了 我有正事要办
No need for that now, I've got the real thing.

1644
01:29:10,850 --> 01:29:12,640
- 我有工作要做 - 夏洛克
- I have work to do. - Sherlock...

1645
01:29:14,390 --> 01:29:15,680
答应我
promise me.

1646
01:29:17,510 --> 01:29:18,930
你还站在这里干什么
What are you still doing here?

1647
01:29:18,930 --> 01:29:21,430
你快帮我弄个赦免令什么的啊
Shouldn't you be off getting me a pardon or something,

1648
01:29:21,430 --> 01:29:22,720
像个大哥该有的样子
like a proper big brother?

1649
01:29:28,090 --> 01:29:29,470
华生医生
Dr. Watson...

1650
01:29:33,720 --> 01:29:35,140
照顾好他
Look after him.

1651
01:29:36,800 --> 01:29:38,390
拜托了
Please.

1652
01:29:59,630 --> 01:30:02,800
夏洛克 等等 解释一下 莫里亚蒂还活着吗
Sherlock, hang on, explain. Moriarty's alive, then?

1653
01:30:02,800 --> 01:30:05,010
我没说他还活着 我是说他回来了
I never said he was alive, I said he was back.

1654
01:30:05,010 --> 01:30:06,460
那他死了吗
So he's dead?

1655
01:30:06,470 --> 01:30:07,650
他当然死了
Of course he's dead, he

1656
01:30:07,650 --> 01:30:10,010
他脑袋都开花了 不可能活下来
blew his own brains out, no-one survives that.

1657
01:30:10,010 --> 01:30:13,670
我刚为了证明这一点 还服药过量了
I just went to the trouble of an overdose to prove it.

1658
01:30:13,670 --> 01:30:16,170
莫里亚蒂死了 这毋庸置疑
Moriarty is dead, no question.

1659
01:30:17,630 --> 01:30:21,420
但重要的是 我很清楚他接下来 要做什么事情
But more importantly, I know exactly what he's going to do next.

1660
01:30:32,590 --> 01:30:33,710
航空器
Flying machines,

1661
01:30:33,710 --> 01:30:36,130
还有什么 电话工具
these, er, telephone contraptions?

1662
01:30:36,130 --> 01:30:37,840
都是些什么疯狂的幻想啊
What sort of lunatic fantasy is that?

1663
01:30:37,840 --> 01:30:39,120
这只是我对
It was simply my conjecture

1664
01:30:39,120 --> 01:30:40,920
未来世界
of what a future world might look like

1665
01:30:40,920 --> 01:30:43,500
还有你和我在其中的猜测
and how you and I might fit inside it.

1666
01:30:43,500 --> 01:30:45,880
逻辑学家能从一滴掉落的水珠
From a drop of water a logician should be able to infer

1667
01:30:45,880 --> 01:30:48,540
推测出它是来自大西洋 还是尼亚加拉河
the possibility of an Atlantic or a Niagara.

1668
01:30:48,540 --> 01:30:50,130
或者是莱辛巴赫瀑布
Or a Reichenbach?

1669
01:30:50,130 --> 01:30:51,930
这件你极度重视的案子 写好了吗
Have you written up your account of the case?

1670
01:30:52,070 --> 01:30:54,250
当然
Yes.

1671
01:30:54,250 --> 01:30:57,330
修改后是我罕见未能破获的案子 对吧
Modified to put it down as one of my rare failures, of course?

1672
01:30:57,350 --> 01:30:58,350
是的
Of course.

1673
01:31:01,460 --> 01:31:03,420
隐形军队的
The Adventure Of...

1674
01:31:03,420 --> 01:31:04,790
大冒险
The Invisible Army.

1675
01:31:06,790 --> 01:31:08,080
复仇女神
The League Of Furies?

1676
01:31:09,210 --> 01:31:11,250
还是恐怖军团
The Monstrous Regiment?

1677
01:31:11,250 --> 01:31:14,650
我更喜欢可恶的新娘
I rather thought The Abominable Bride.

1678
01:31:15,350 --> 01:31:16,350
有点骇人听闻
A trifle lurid.

1679
01:31:16,370 --> 01:31:18,560
但肯定畅销 它里面还有谋杀呢
It'll sell. It's got proper murders in it too.

1680
01:31:18,670 --> 01:31:19,960
你是专家嘛
You're the expert.

1681
01:31:19,960 --> 01:31:23,160
至于你的故事
As for your own tale,

1682
01:31:23,160 --> 01:31:27,040
你确定只用了百分之七的溶液吗
are you sure it's still just a 7% solution that you take?

1683
01:31:27,040 --> 01:31:29,250
我认为你可能加大了剂量
I think you may have increased the dosage.

1684
01:31:29,250 --> 01:31:31,540
或许我想象力太丰富了
Perhaps I was being a little fanciful.

1685
01:31:32,660 --> 01:31:35,250
但或许这些事真的会实现
But perhaps such things could come to pass.

1686
01:31:36,660 --> 01:31:39,410
无论如何 我相信自己 会很适应那个世界
In any case, I know I would be very much at home in such a world.

1687
01:31:39,410 --> 01:31:42,160
- 我不认为我能 - 我可不这样认为
- Huh, I don't think I would be. - I beg to differ.

1688
01:31:44,000 --> 01:31:46,570
但我一直知道自己 是超越时代的人
But then I've always known I was a man out of his time.

